title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes (serving for 12) as on box. Blend in rest of ingredients.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh fruit bowl
directions: In a large bowl, combine melon cubes and corn syrup.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, stir in remaining fruit.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves if desired.
Yields 3 to 4 quarts.

title: southern muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk until flour mixture is moist.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Yield: 12 muffins.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour; measure
and
re-sift 3 times with soda and salt. Melt chocolate
over
hot
water;
cool.
Cream fat and sugar. Add sugar
and
eggs
and
beat until fluffy.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla, then stir
in
coffee or water.
Bake in lined 8-inch tins or muffin tins.
Bake at 325° or 350°.

title: baline (potato pancake)
directions: Put potatoes and onion through a blender.

Add the egg, baking powder and flour (as needed to hold other ingredients together). Shape into patties and fry in fat (just so covered) until brown. These may also be stuffed with cheese for a variety.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables; when done add corn and carrots.
Add 1 pint half and half and 1 cup squeeze cheese.
Add more milk if desired.

title: maraschino cherries
directions: Soak cherries overnight in brine of 2 quarts water, salt and alum (best for 24 hours).
Next morning, drain cherries and rinse in cold water.
Combine cherries with 3 cups water, sugar, food coloring and lemon juice.
Heat to boiling, then let set 24 hours. Again bring to boil; let set 24 hours.
Bring to boil again.
On the third day after letting set 24 hours, add 1 ounce of almond extract.
Seal while hot.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl combine 3/4 c. sugar, flour, 3 Tbsp. cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted butter, and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into square pan, 8x8x2-inch or 9x9x2-inch.
In small bowl combine remaining 1/2 c. sugar, brown sugar and remaining 4 Tbsp. cocoa. Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top, do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes or until center is ALMOST set.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Spoon into desert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Garnish as desired.

title: huevos rancheros
directions: In skillet with oil over slow heat, add all ingredients, except eggs, within 1 minute.
Add eggs, scramble and enjoy with refried beans and tortillas if you were brave enough to include the jalapeno.
Sit down by yourself and enjoy, as no one else will want to make a trip to the creek with you.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and cool in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with any fresh fruit.

title: holiday lobster spread
directions: In a medium saucepan, sprinkle unflavored gelatine over water and lemon juice.
Let stand for 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
With wire whip or rotary beater, blend in sour cream, chili sauce and horseradish; fold in lobster or shrimp.
Turn into a party mold pan.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers or party bread. Makes about 3 1/2 cups of spread.

title: laura's spaghetti pie
directions: Add butter, Parmesan cheese, and eggs to spaghetti.
Form mixture into buttered pie plate.
Spread on cottage cheese.
Cook ground beef, green pepper and onions; drain.
Add tomatoes, paste, sugar and seasonings.
Spoon onto spaghetti crust.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 5 minutes longer, or until cheese melts.

title: white sauce
directions: In a small saucepan melt margarine or butter.
Stir in flour, saltand pepper.
Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 minute more. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: pastel party pie
directions: Add water to juice of berries to make 2 1/2 cups.
Heat to boiling.
Dissolve jello in hot liquid.
Add 1 quart vanilla ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring, until melted.
Chill until thick, not set.
Fold in berries.
Pour into pie shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Pull chicken off the bone and place in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour on top of chicken.
Crush crackers and melt butter.
Combine and spread on top of soup. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: dutch "reuben" sandwich
directions: Shoestring or julienne the ham and cheese; just get it into thin strips.
Mix ham, cheese and sauerkraut.
Add parsley and caraway seed to taste and enough mayonnaise to mix well.
Serve on pumpernickel bread.
This is also good grilled.
This is a rather small amount, so you may want to double it.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt oleo over low heat, stir in cocoa.
In small bowl beat egg with wire whisk; add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour this in cocoa mixture and heat while stirring.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mixture does not need to come to boil, just heat until well blended.

title: my mom's cookies
directions: Add salt if shortening is used.

title: chickin lickin' sandwiches
directions: Empty chicken into 1-quart casserole dish.
Add soup; mix well.
Add potato chips; mix.
Cover with lid and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir mixture.
Return to oven and microwave on High for 2 more minutes or until dish is warmed through.
Serve on buns.

title: sweet fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender.
Blend until smooth.
Chill at least one hour.
Serve with assorted fruits. Makes about 4 cups.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mash pineapple and peaches together in a colander; let drain. Mix milk and ReaLemon together.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into two 9-inch graham cracker shells.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry streusel coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups dry cake mix.
Reserve the rest for topping.
Take 1 1/2 cups cake mix, flour, yeast, eggs and warm water and beat 2 minutes.
Spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Combine reserved cake mix with margarine and sugar to make topping.
Spoon filling over dough, then put on topping.
Bake immediately at 325°.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients except rolls and lettuce leaves; chill.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and chop onion and green pepper in large container.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture while hot.
Do not stir.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours in airtight container.
Keeps for at least 2 weeks.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Grease an oblong baking dish and mix rice, soup and milk together.
Pour into dish (10 x 14-inches).
Rinse out both soup cans with a can of milk each.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: iced coffee
directions: Brew extra strong coffee.
Pour over ice cubes.
Add additional cold water until desired strength.
Serve with sugar, if desired.

title: mother's apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well.
Add apples last.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in a greased tube pan.
Needs no topping.

title: brownies
directions: In a saucepan, combine butter, water and cocoa.
Cook and stir until mix comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and set aside.
In bowl, stir flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir batter into hot cocoa mix.
By hand, beat until well mixed.

title: vinegar beans
directions: Mix well and cook 40 minutes.

title: egg strata
directions: Trim crust off bread slices.
Place in a greased casserole. Place cheese on top of bread.
Beat rest of ingredients together and pour over the bread.
Let set 1 hour, then bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pound cake(with coconut sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add "Adams Best" vanilla and Adams butter flavoring.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well. (Use high speed with electric mixer.)
Sift flour and salt together, then add slowly.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into a 10-inch stem pan that has been well-greased and dusted with flour. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Make Coconut Sauce about 5 or 10 minutes before cake is done.

title: mom's award winning meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, using 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Place in an oiled baking dish.
Cover with remaining tomato sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Chill before serving.

title: "easy-tasty" lime mold salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool and add fruit and nuts. Mix well.
Fold in sour cream last.
Put in mold and chill several hours.
Makes 8 to 10 large servings.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Grease 11 x 16-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with unbroken graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
In saucepan, mix butter and margarine until melted.
Add sugar. Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Drizzle over graham crackers and nuts.
Bake for 10 minutes in 325° oven. Let cool in pan.
Break into pieces.

title: fruit chewies
directions: Cut 2 bananas into medium size chunks.
Mash the third banana. Combine all ingredients and stir until mixed.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: oven honey chicken
directions: Coat chicken pieces with mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Microwave 1 stick butter on High in a shallow baking dish for 1 minute or until melted.
Arrange chicken in single layer in butter, turning to coat each piece.
Microwave for 10 minutes on High, giving dish a 1/4 turn twice during cooking time.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash bean dip and spread on large plate. Peel and mash avocado with lemon juice, salt and pepper, then spread on top of bean dip. Mix sour cream, mayo and taco mix. Spread on top of avocado, then sprinkle on onions, olives, green peppers and tomatoes. Top with cheese. Serve with taco chips.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix oleo, cake mix and coconut.
Put in oblong cake pan; slightly pat in bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour drained pie apples on this hot crust.
Mix cinnamon and sugar; sprinkle over apples.
Mix egg and sour cream; drizzle over top. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: party dip
directions: Mix all together. Chill. Good as a vegetable dip or chips and snacks.

title: rice plus
directions: Melt butter.
Add rice and mushrooms.
Saute until lightly browned. Stir in soup mix and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 20 minutes until all liquid is absorbed.

title: broiled salisbury steak
directions: Combine ground beef and remaining ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into patties.
Place on broiler pan.
Broil for 5 minutes on each side.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut butter chex
directions: Melt peanut butter chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Stir until smooth.
Place the Rice Chex in a large bowl and pour peanut butter mixture over them.
Toss gently to cover Chex completely. Use a larger container with a lid or a large plastic bag, put coated Chex in and add 1 box xxx sugar.
Toss gently.

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Add milk to beaten eggs, stirring to blend.
Sift together flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Gradually add to egg mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: grape frost
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
Serve at once.
Yields 2 servings.

title: lucy's french cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar with an electric mixer until sugar no longer looks granular.
Mix in egg yolks, vanilla, sour cream, lemon juice and grated lemon rind.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold gently, but well, into cheese mixture.
Pour into lightly baked pastry-lined spring-form pan.

title: bucket bread
directions: Pour boiling water over the fruit.
Add soda and oleo and stir well.
Let stand until completely cold.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour 7 (No. 303) cans.
Fill 1/2 full; bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
If not brown enough, raise heat.
Hit side of can with hand to loosen. Remove from can for cooling.

title: spicy mexican
directions: About 45 minutes before serving over medium heat, in a 12-inch skillet, cook beef, onion and green peppers (1/2 cup) until meat is browned, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Drain tomato liquid into meat mixture, cut tomatoes into bite sized pieces and set aside.
Add macaroni, sugar, chili powder, salt and 1 cup water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream; sprinkle on reserved green peppers and tomatoes. Cook until heated through.
Makes 7 servings.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Refrigerate.
Before serving, add sliced bananas and Cool Whip.

title: chicken with broccoli bake
directions: Melt margarine; add flour, soup, cheese and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Then add broccoli and chicken.
Heat just until boiling; take off heat and add sour cream.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with rest of Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
(Carrots go well with this.)

title: lemon snowballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cream butter with sugar.
Add flour, cornstarch and salt; mix in lemon rind.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in nuts, pressing them in.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Drizzle with Lemon Frosting.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients in large bowl. Pour 1/2-3/4 bottle of dressing over mixture. Stir well and refrigerate. Make this the day before for more flavor. Before serving you may need to add a little more dressing. Serves about 20 people.

title: mrs. e. buchholz perfect dill pickles
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients 15 minutes.
Pack cukes in jars with lots of dill.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar to each quart (do not boil the sugar).
Pour the boiling vinegar brine over cukes.
Fill jars and seal tight.
Set jars in boiling water to come over tops of the jars.
Let stand until cold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and 1/2 cup pecans.
Form ball and roll in the 1/2 cup ground pecans.
Chill overnight, then let warm up to room temperature to serve.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut zucchini in 1/2-inch slices; parboil in salt water for 5 minutes and drain.
Place in greased shallow casserole.
dish. Slice onion thin and place on top of zucchini.
Pour 2 teaspoons of melted butter over top.
Pepper to taste.
Cover with cheese, then spread sauce over the cheese.
Top with the bread crumbs. Drizzle remaining butter over the bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until onion is done.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef while cooking noodles.
Drain beef and then stir in sauce.
Add the spices. Simmer beef and sauce 5 to 10 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas supreme
directions: In a medium bowl, mix chicken, Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and 1/2 cup sour cream together.
Divide into 8 portions and place on flour tortillas.
Roll up tortillas and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with enchilada sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and black olives.

title: hot cherry jello
directions: Prepare jello as directed.
Melt red hots in 1 c. hot water. Add red hots, apples and celery when jello is partially set. Chill.

title: ginger beef stew
directions: Place meat in casserole.
Mix next 5 ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: stuffed cheese bacon potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400°.
Remove from oven, cut in lengthwise slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out inside and mash with sour cream, Blue cheese, milk, butter, salt and pepper. Whip until fluffy.
Spoon mixture into potato shells.
Place on baking sheet; return to oven for 15 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.

title: fettucine with shrimp sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, wine, marjoram and dash of pepper; bring to boiling.
Add shrimp.
Return mixture to boiling. Cook 1 minute or until shrimp are tender.
Remove shrimp.
Cover and set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix and pour in large 10 x 14-inch pan.
Then cut enough apples to cover dough (about 1-inch thick).
Pour on 1 cup sugar. Then add crumb mixture.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Keeps for several days.

title: spinach salad
directions: Thaw spinach.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese, cottage cheese and mayonnaise together thoroughly. Mix jello and hot water.
Add vinegar.
Add vegetables and cheese mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased mold.
Will jell quickly once in mold.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in water until tender.
Drain and add eggs, mayonnaise, onion and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Put bread crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: four day sweet pickles
directions: Thinly slice one gallon cucumbers.
Place in large crock or nonmetal container.
In separate pan, bring to boil one gallon water and salt.
Pour over cucumbers.
Weigh cucumbers down (i.e. cover with a plate turned upside-down and anchor with any clean heavy object to prevent floating).
Leave for 4 days.

title: spicy tortilla roll-ups
directions: Beat cream cheese in mixing bowl until light.
Add olives, onions and tomatoes; beat well.
Spread over tortillas; roll to enclose filling.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Slice and arrange on serving platter.
Makes 24 servings.

title: pearl cookies
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Add remaining ingredients except for half of sugar.
Form dough into small balls.
Roll in remaining powdered sugar.
Yields 30 balls.

title: heath bars
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in bottom of cookie sheet; spread to coat bottom of pan.
Line bottom of pan with whole graham crackers.
Bring 1 cup margarine and 1 cup brown sugar to a boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers and top with 1 cup nuts. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Sprinkle top with package of chocolate chips.
Let set for 5 minutes and spread.
Cut while warm and refrigerate.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Sift sugar, cornstarch and cocoa into saucepan.
Add milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add 2 tablespoons cornstarch to beaten eggs and stir in.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Pour into crust.
Serve with whipped topping.
Good while still warm.

title: merk's coffee cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add eggs, singly, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, blending well after each addition.
Spread half of batter into tube pan, greased and floured.
Cream brown sugar, the margarine and cinnamon together; add nuts and mix well.
Dot batter with 1/2 of this mixture.
Put rest of batter on top and sprinkle balance of mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Eat or refrigerate right away.

title: cherry chip coconut cake
directions: Beat margarine and Crisco until light and creamy.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Pour into four 9-inch cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: refrigerator fruit cake
directions: Crush crackers; melt marshmallows in a double boiler and pour over crackers.
Add cream, fruit and nuts.
Mix and pack in cracker box.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours before cutting.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: (Music:)

God's appointment, God's joy and praise, God's glory, God's gift of talent, God's glimpse of heavenly choirs, God's sense of humor, God's sense of rhythm, God's perception of harmony, God's enjoyment for mankind, God's outlet of expression, God given breath to support God's creation.

title: hot macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package, then drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Add next ingredients and mix.
Stir in half the cheese.
Crush crackers and stir in melted butter.
Set aside. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top of casserole.
Spread cracker mixture on top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: granny's cornbread salad
directions: Crumble cornbread into large bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp. Crumble bacon and with with onion, pepper and tomato. Add to cornbread.
Pour hot bacon grease over mixture until slightly moist and vigorously toss with fork.
Goes great with beans.
It's finger lickin' good.

title: "aeblekage"(danish apple cake)
directions: Brown crumbs well in a skillet with butter and sugar.
Place prepared crumbs in a serving dish in layers, alternately with cooled tart applesauce.
Allow to harden in refrigerator.
Serve cold with generous whipped cream topping, sweetened.
Decorate with dabs of jelly.

title: punch
directions: *May add Fifth of Peach Schnapps.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Put flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Melt margarine in one cup of boiling water.
Pour over dry ingredients plus 1 cup of cold water.
Then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 10 x 13-inch pan, as it can't be removed from pan.
Batter is very thin.

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage, peppers and onions; drain.
Roll out bread dough (like you would for pizza).
Spread sausage on rolled out bread dough.
Sprinkle with cheese and pepper mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: ready after church chicken and rice
directions: Salt and pepper chicken and lay in greased 9 x 13-inch pan (or larger) skin side down.
Pour rice around chicken.
Crumble bouillon cubes in water to dissolve; pour into pan.
Cover with foil and seal tightly.
Depending on how long you will be gone, cook 4 hours at 250°, 3 hours at 275°, 2 1/2 hours at 300°, 2 hours at 325° or 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with cranberry sauce and Bread-Ready-Quick.

title: bell pepper nachos
directions: Cut bell pepper strips crosswise into halves. Arrange close together in ungreased broiler-proof pie pan, 9 x 1 1/4-inch or round pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inch.
Sprinkle with cheese, olives and red pepper.
Set oven control to broil.
Broil peppers with tops 3 to 4-inches from heat about 3 minutes or until cheese is melted. Makes 6 servings (6 nachos each).
Contains 3 g fat, 50 calories and 4 g protein.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion together.
Add mushroom soup and water to meat.
Add seasoning to taste.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice, pasta or potatoes.

title: steamboat apple dumplings
directions: Have oven hot, above 500°.
Put water and sugar on the stove to boil in large pan.
Pare apples.
Put flour, lard and salt in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Put soda in buttermilk, stir until it foams.
Add to flour mixture.
(It may take a little more buttermilk.)
Make dumplings.
Drop in boiling syrup.
Let boil 3 or 4 minutes, while mixing 1 teaspoon flour in a little water. Pour around dumplings.
Let boil up well.
Dot with butter. Put in oven and bake until brown.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In heavy skillet, brown chicken in hot oil.
Combine spaghetti sauce mix with wine; pour over chicken.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer another 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: zucchini pineapple
directions: Peel zucchini, take out seeds and grate, cube or slice.
Cook all ingredients until tender.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: venison roast
directions: Soak roast in salt water overnight.
Rinse well.
Place venison neck in roasting pan, sprinkle roast with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
I use a lot of pepper and garlic.
Place tomato pieces and onions over roast and secure with toothpicks.
Pour tomato juice and wine over roast, lay bacon across the top, cover and bake at 325° for approximately 3 to 4 hours or until meat falls off the bone.
About 1 1/2 hours before roast is done, add potatoes and carrots.
Don't forget to baste periodically.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine sugar and cornstarch in medium bowl.
Add eggs, corn and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Dot top with butter.
Bake 1 hour or until pudding is set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Add nuts.
Bake one hour in loaf pan.

title: river boat shrimp
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter or margarine until soft.
Add drained tomatoes and seasoning.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add uncooked shrimp.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste and cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Gently stir in rice and well drained peas.
Cover and immediately serve.
Makes enough for 6 to 8 people.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Pour off dressing in pickles and slice.
To pickles add sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Stir; refrigerate.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Use a microwave-safe dish with lid.
Wash apple, cut and core. Cut into slices, peel and then cut into bite-size pieces.
Put in casserole dish.
Squeeze 1 to 2 tablespoons of margarine evenly over the apple pieces.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of brown sugar. Sprinkle 2 teaspoons cinnamon over the apples.
Stir to coat the apples evenly.
Cover the apples.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.

title: mini cheese balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in medium bowl and blend well. Shape mixture into small balls or roll into cylinder.
Coat with sesame seed.
Cover with foil or plastic wrap and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: alabama camp stew
directions: Cook meat until it is tender and falls apart.
Then add everything but corn; add it when all other ingredients are done.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar and vanilla. Blend well, then add boiling water.
Beat until very stiff.

title: brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13-inch round pizza pan.
Combine brownie mix, egg, oil and water in large bowl.
Stir with spoon until well blended, about 50 strokes.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 23 to 27 minutes; cool completely.
tags: brownies plus milk chocolate chunks mix

title: cake that doesn't stay around
directions: Mix dry ingredients and make a well in the mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring but not beating dough.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chuck wagon hurry-up
directions: Brown beef in a skillet.
Add salt, pepper and onions.
Cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add tomatoes and beans.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with biscuits.
Recipe serves 4.

title: ben getti
directions: Brown meat and onions lightly.
Cook noodles in salt water. Add all together.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix all together until blended.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 10-inch pan for 35 minutes at 350°. Put marshmallows on top when cake is done.
Place back in oven until softened.
Then frost cake.

title: fat-free mashed potatoes
directions: Put onion and garlic in cooking pan with potatoes.
Add enough water to cover potatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Remove the onion and garlic.
Drain the potatoes in a colander until thoroughly drained.
Pat dry, if necessary, to remove excess moisture.
Cut potatoes into chunks and mash by hand or use electric mixer.
Mash potatoes until free of lumps.
Add the desired amount of evaporated skim milk and whip until creamy. Season with pepper to taste.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, saute onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic in oil until tender (about 10 minutes).
Stir in tomato sauce, water, Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook for 5 minutes or until shrimp is done.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: herbal stuffing chicken
directions: Preheat oven
to
Coat chicken breasts with sour cream and then
roll in stuffing mix to cover chicken.
Melt 1 stick of butter.
Place
chicken in baking dish.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Place water, yeast, sugar and oil in cup; set aside.
Place flour and soda in glass bowl.
Pour buttermilk over flour.
Add yeast, oil and water.
Mix.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Use as needed.
Keeps up to three weeks.

title: spiced pears
directions: Heat syrup from pears and cinnamon candies until melted. Place pear halves, rounded side down, in a flat shallow dish. Pour syrup over pears and set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain on waxed paper before serving.
Thin cream cheese with milk.
Place pears on a bed of lettuce.
Place a scoop of the thinned cream cheese in each pear half.
Dribble each pear with French dressing.

title: prune fudge
directions: Wash prunes; cover with water and cook slowly until tender. Drain, pit and chop.
Add sugar to prune juice.
Add prunes and lemon juice.
Boil to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Cool to room temperature.
Beat until creamy.
Add nuts.
Pour into well buttered, shallow pan.
Cut in squares.

title: bert diamond's mandel broit
directions: Beat eggs with fork, adding sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix baking powder into one of the cups of flour.
Then combine with rest of flour.
Alternate flour and oil into eggs and sugar mixture.
Place bowl of dough in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Using flour to handle dough, cut dough into 4 sections.
Stretch and shape each section until it is about 8-inches long.
Sprinkle cinnamon-sugar mixture over each loaf.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Take out; cut in diagonal strips.
Turn sideways; put back for 10 minutes, then turn on other side for 10 minutes more.

title: cherry yum yum pie
directions: Cream milk and cream cheese.
Gradually add lemon juice and vanilla.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Chill well before topping with cherry pie filling.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with 1 cup of the milk.
Bring to boil and stir until thick.
Beat eggs and add to other cup of milk.
Stir into the thickened mixture.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix well. Store in jar. To make tea use 2 teaspoons mix per cup.

title: special country ham
directions: Put country ham in a 9
x 13-inch baking dish and add 3/4 to 1 can of Coke and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: marilyn's beef and rice
directions: Cook ground beef in a little water.
Pour in rice and onion soup mix and cook until rice is done.
Add salt and pepper.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese; add rest of ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Chill, then form into ball and roll in chopped pecans; chill again.
Serve with crackers.

title: barrett dill pickles
directions: Put vinegar and spices in a 2-quart glass container.
Cut pickles in 1/2-inch chunks and add to the container.
Pour in sugar on top.
Do not mix!
Screw on lid and refrigerate for 10 days.
For the second batch, use the same liquid once more and add 1 cup sugar on top as before.

title: breakfast sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and onion and set aside.
Combine egg and milk; add Bisquick.
Stir until moistened.
Add sausage and onion mixture and half of the cheese.
Spread in baking pan.
Top with remaining cheese, butter and poppy seed.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Mix with other ingredients.
(Save some noodles for topping.)
Put mixture in ungreased casserole dish.
Top with noodles.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemonade with splenda
directions: Mash lemon slices, lemon juice and Splenda with fork or spoon in tall glass.
Add club soda and ice cubes.
Garnish with mint leaves and serve.
Makes 1 (8 fluid ounces) serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed; drain.
(Add a small amount of butter or oil to prevent sticking.)
Saute vegetables in garlic powder and butter about 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add basil, salt and pepper.
Stir into pasta.
Add Italian dressing to taste. Toss well.
Can sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: cottage cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Mix crumbs and sugar together well. Add melted butter and mix well; spread on bottom of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan and pack down well.
Mix next 3 ingredients and beat well.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt together until thick and light in color.
Add lemon juice and vanilla and beat well.
Add to cheese mixture and beat well; pour into spring-form pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.
Turn off heat but allow cake to remain in oven with door closed for 1 hour longer.
Allow cake to cool before removing side of pan.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan, add lemon juice and sugar. Heat to boiling, soak gelatin for 5 minutes in 1 C cold water. Combine two mixtures, chill until thickened.

title: nonroll pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Add oil and milk.
Mix together and press into 9-inch pie tin.
Prick well.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 18 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Peel and dice potatoes very small.
Put raw potatoes in top double boiler or crock pot.
Cut up and add butter, salt and pepper.
Cover with cream just covering potatoes.
Simmer covered about 4 hours until potatoes are soft.
Stir during cooking to mix.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pecans and coconut; sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Pour prepared cake mix over pecan and coconut mixture.

title: chocolate raspberry crumb bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Beat butter until creamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and salt until well mixed.
With floured fingers, press 1 3/4 c. of mixture onto bottom of greased 9x13 pan, reserve remaining crumb mix.
Bake 10-12 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Then add remaining ingredients.

title: marinated fiddlehead salad
directions: Gently toss fiddleheads, onion and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients for marinade in large bowl.
Add fiddleheads, pepper and onion.
Marinate for 24 hours.

title: microbaked brown rice
directions: In heavy, microwavable casserole dish, brown rice in butter until grains are coated with butter and begin to sizzle.
Add broth, bay leaf and thyme (or allspice); season to taste with salt and pepper.
Bring to boil on High; simmer until tender (10 to 12 minutes).
Stir; cover and let stand.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: tuna fritters
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until crisp.

title: cinnamon apple cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add apples and nuts and mix.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Prepare a casserole pan by spraying bottom and sides with olive oil Pam.
Wash chicken thoroughly and pat dry.
Lay chicken on flat surface and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Next, sprinkle with dry seasonings.
Place chicken in cooking pan and spread the cream of mushroom soup over chicken breasts.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, eggs, peas, green pepper, onion and bacon in order.
Mix together salad dressing and sugar; spread on salad. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Better if made a day before serving.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: The parsley and mushrooms are optional.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Arrange broccoli in long dish and pour sauce over broccoli. Sprinkle on Pepperidge Farm Herb Bread Crumbs.
Bake at 325 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: eggs and ham brunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Place bread, ham and cheese in dish.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard and pour over contents of dish.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In large bowl, whisk together yogurt, dill, garlic, lemon juice and salt.
Add sliced cucumbers.
Toss gently to coat well. Cover and chill at least 30 minutes until ready to serve.
Toss gently just before serving.
Garnish with dill sprig.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Batter and fry steaks like usual.
Take soup and water and put in crock-pot.
Add steaks and let it simmer for 2 or 3 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Drain grease off and add tomatoes, paste and catsup.
Mix in noodles and put in casserole dish.
Grate some Velveeta cheese on top and sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top of cheese.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: tuaca banshee
directions: Mix equal parts of Tuaca, creme de cacao and Kahlua.
Add half and half.
Blend and then strain.
Pour in sour glass.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green chillies.
Stir in Cheez Whiz, salsa and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with taco or nacho chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk and mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Take off heat, add butter and vanilla.
Pour half of pudding over vanilla wafers and sliced bananas in layers until all used up.
Add beaten egg whites on top, place under broiler until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Cream sugars, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Measure oatmeal and then blend baking powder with oatmeal.
Add to moist mixture. Add chips, nuts and grated Hershey bar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes in golf ball size mounds.
Makes approximately 8 to 9 dozen cookies.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Cook ground beef; saute onions and garlic.
Add other ingredients.
Put everything together in big baking dish.
Preheat oven to 300°.

title: chow mein noodles
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cup
directions: Drain canned fruit; add strawberries to the drained fruit and stir in dry instant pudding.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: mushroom chicken bake
directions: Place in chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprayed with Pam.
Combine undiluted soups, sour cream and mushrooms.
Then pour over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs.

title: danish meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Brown evenly and drain.

title: banana crunchy split
directions: Put chopped nuts and cookies in a bowl.
Roll chocolate scoop of ice cream into the mixture.
Do the same with the other scoops of ice cream.
Add banana slices.
Pour on the chocolate syrup. Now add the whipped cream and the cherry.
Makes one sundae.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Reserve
cup cookie crumbs and 1/4 cup pecans.
In trifle dish,
layer
1/2	of
the
cookies, 1/2 of the sliced bananas, 1/2 of the nuts, 1/2 of the syrup and cover with 1/2 of
the Cool Whip.
Repeat and sprinkle with reserved nuts and cookie crumbs. Chill.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: puri(bread)
directions: Mix wheat flour with water to make a dough.
Let it stand for 30 minutes.
Make small balls and roll it thin in round shapes. Deep fry until they become light brown. Serve with vegetable or meat curry.

title: party potato puff
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add potatoes and beat until thoroughly blended and fluffy.
Add egg, onion, pimiento, salt and pepper and mix well.
Spoon into a lightly buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, pizza sauce, herbs and spices.
Mix. Simmer 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a bowl, place everything except lettuce.
Stir in dressing to taste.
It is best if made day ahead.
Add lettuce just before serving.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening and peanut butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Blend in syrup and milk.
Shape into 2-inch rolls.
Chill.
Slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Place half the slices on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spread each with 1/2 teaspoon peanut butter.
Cover with remaining slices.
Seal with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place beef, potatoes, carrots and onion in deep casserole dish.
Mix soup and water and pour over all.
Bake at 275 degrees for 3 1/2 hours.
This is not a thick sauce; excellent served with cornbread.

title: dried apple fritters
directions: Combine the apples with enough flour to make a stiff batter, then shape into flat cakes.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown on both sides.
Drain and sprinkle with sugar.
Serve warm.

title: horseradish sauce for roast beef
directions: Add salt, pepper, mustard and vinegar to horseradish.
Mix thoroughly. Fold cream into the ingredients, cover and refrigerate for 3 or more hours.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Sift and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Put 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: western beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Fry out the bacon; drain any excess grease.
Mix all ingredients and place in baking dish; bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin pie(heritage recipe)
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in 2 or 3 pie shells (according to the size of the crusts).

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Using food processor or electric mixer, combine and blend cream cheese, sour cream, oregano and garlic powder until smooth. Spread cream cheese mixture in 9 or 10-inch pie pan or quiche dish.
Spoon pizza sauce on cream cheese.
Sprinkle pepperoni and green pepper on sauce layer.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; sprinkle with shredded cheeses and bake an additional 5 minutes. Serve with crackers or sweet pepper strips.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with 1 package Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: oven-barbecued cranberry chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Cook onion and celery in oil until tender.
Stir in cranberry sauce and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and pour over chicken that you have put in a baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
I do not use the oil; I use Pam.
The last 20 to 30 minutes, I take chicken out and add to the sauce 1 to 2 boxes Rice-A-Roni long grain wild rice that I have already fixed like box says, but I leave the margarine out.
I then lay chicken back on and finish cooking.
I also use chicken breast.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream
margarine,
oil	and
sugar.
Add
eggs one at a time, then extract.
Add alternately the flour and 7-Up.	Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Peel sweet potatoes.
Cover with water and boil until tender. Drain.
Add oleo and mash while hot.
Add sugar, beaten eggs, milk, vanilla and spice.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until firm.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, egg and margarine.
Add soda, salt, cream of tartar and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in flour

title: stroganoff noodles and meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs and water. Shape into 16 (1-inch) meatballs.
In 10-inch skillet, heat oil and cook meatballs over medium heat 5 minutes or until done; set aside.
In medium saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups water and milk to the boiling point.
Stir in noodles and stroganoff sauce and continue boiling over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 7 minutes.
Stir in mushrooms, parsley and meatballs and continue cooking, stirring frequently, 3 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: chinese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, top with vinegar and oil dressing.

title: pineapple-marshmallow dessert
directions: Place the marshmallows, milk and pineapple juice in a double boiler over boiling water until marshmallows melt.
When cool, add the whipped cream and drained crushed pineapple.
Place part of the graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan leaving some to place on the top.
Pour in the first mixture, then cover with the rest of crackers.
Let stand in refrigerator all night.
Serves 16.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Cook dates, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add walnuts; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Divide into 4 parts. Roll; spread filling and roll up.
Freeze for easier cutting. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Bring milk to a scald, soak bread 5 minutes in this.
Add butter, salt and sugar.
Pour slowly over eggs; add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into 3 to 4-quart stainless steel mixing bowl. Bake in pan of hot water at 350° until firm.

title: frosted salad
directions: Mix the lemon and orange jellos with 2 cups hot water and 1 1/2 cups cold water.
When slightly thickened, add crushed pineapple (drained; save juice), bananas, marshmallows and lemon juice.
Chill until firm.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onions until half done.
Drain well.
Mix with chicken soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Grease a large baking dish.
Layer with stuffing mix.
Pour zucchini mixture over this.
Cover with other half of stuffing mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix soup and cheese in small saucepan until cheese melts.
Put green beans in casserole pan.
Pour sauce over and stir.
Crush onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chiffon delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water. Mix vanilla pudding with milk and add to jello mixture.
Jello does not need to set up.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Fold in cut up mandarin oranges.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican starburst casserole
directions: In large skillet heat oil; add green onion and cook until tender.
Add ground beef and chilies; cook until meat is browned. Drain fat.
Stir in soup, water and chili powder.
Heat to boiling, then simmer 10 minutes.

title: candied chex
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the butter, syrup and brown sugar.
Remove from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour over cereal in a large, flat pan and stir well.
Bake at 200° for 60 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt, pineapple and juice.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine brown sugar and pecans and place on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° in tube pan until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Bake 35 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cover. Microwave on High for 9 minutes.

title: cranberry-pecan bars
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine the 1 cup flour and the 2 tablespoons sugar with a pastry cutter.
Cut margarine or butter into the flour mixture until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in 1/2 cup of the pecans.
Press flour mix into the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 10 minutes.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great and quick!

title: chocolate no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients in pan. Boil; bring to soft-ball stage. Remove from heat. Add the oatmeal and vanilla. Drop by tablespoons on wax paper.

title: vegetable fiesta! con queso (with cheese)
directions: Heat oil over medium to high heat.
Add onion, bell pepper, mushrooms and zucchini.
Stir one to two minutes.
Add garlic and oregano.
Stir fry one more minute or until crisp-tender.
Add wine and broth; stir fry a few seconds until evaporated. Add salt to taste.
Remove pan from heat and place cheese slices on top of the vegetables.
Cover the pan for about 2 minutes so the warmth of the vegetables will melt the cheese.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Sift the dry ingredients and set aside.
Melt butter in boiling water; add sugar, pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, egg, vanilla and nuts, all in the same bowl, and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing only until flour disappears.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Use 1 pound loaf pan.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Cook the eggs, flour, sugar and pineapple juice until thick.
Cool.
Add pineapple, diced oranges and marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Add coconut, if wanted.
Let stand and chill at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: eggplant appetizer(baba ghannuj)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and remove stem of eggplant. Pierce with a fork about 5 times.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove from oven and run under cold water.

title: broccoli and cauliflower soup
directions: Cook in small amount of salted water until tender.
Mash until very fine.
Then add cream of mushroom, cream of chicken, milk and Velveeta cheese.
Let warm until cheese melts.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: hamburger cheese pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion; drain.
Arrange meat mixture and cheese in pie shell.
Beat together mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch, eggs, salt and pepper until blended, using rotary beater.
Pour mixture into shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Makes 6 servings.

title: liz's marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Ready to use on any meat.

title: hawaiian delight wedding cake
directions: Grease a flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook cake at 325° for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Add cream cheese to pudding.
Mix well.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle pineapple on pudding mix.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Garnish with sliced almonds and sliced cherries.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and Karo.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Add pecans and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 420°.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until filling does not shake.
Do not overcook.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Slice peppers lengthwise.
Spread over bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper in a bowl; beat well.
Spread over cheese.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Cut into small squares.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine the first four ingredients until crumbly; press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Meanwhile, beat pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and salt in a mixing bowl until smooth. Pour over crust. Bake for 45 minutes. Combine brown sugar, pecans and butter; sprinkle over the top. Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool. Store in refrigerator.

title: surprise peach salad
directions: Put jello into saucepan with sugar and add pineapple with juice and bring to boil.
Let boil a few minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together until smooth.
Chill and serve with chips or crackers.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown onions and meat.
Add gravy, mushrooms and onion soup. Divide all (including potatoes and carrots) between 2 deep dish pie shells.
Top with regular pie shell.
Slit top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken pieces in water containing extra onion and celery.
Saute onion, celery and carrots in margarine for 10 minutes.
Add flour to vegetables, stirring well.
Cook one minute, stirring constantly.
Combine broth (use broth from cooked chicken and add 2 teaspoons chicken bouillon to
it) and milk. Gradually add this to the vegetable mixture, stirring constantly over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Stir in salt and pepper. Add chicken; stir well.
Pour into a well-greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with pastry crust.
Cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix in blender.
Put in pie pan and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done. This makes its own crust; you do not need a pie crust.
Very easy made and very delicious.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, putting aside 6 to 7 cookies for top of the salad when all is combined.

title: pepper steak
directions: Trim fat and bone from meat. Cut meat into 4 to 6 serving pieces. Grease large skillet lightly with fat from meat.
Brown meat thoroughly on one side. Turn and season with 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Brown the other side of the meat.
Turn and season with remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Push meat to one section. Add onion. Cook and stir until tender. Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add green peppers.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Blend cornstarch and water. Stir gradually into meat mixture. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Boil 1 minute. Add tomatoes.
Heat through. Serve over rice.

title: pepino molded salad
directions: Soften gelatin in 1 cup of tomato juice.
Bring 3 cups tomato juice to a boil in a non-aluminum saucepan.
Turn off heat and add tomato juice-gelatin mixture; stir until dissolved, about 1 minute.
Add basil, lemon juice and Tabasco; mix well.
Stir in celery, green pepper and carrot into the tomato juice mixture and let cool to room temperature.
Pour into mold and place in refrigerator until set.

title: one-pan potatoes and chicken teriyaki
directions: Microwave potatoes 8 to 10 minutes until tender.
While potatoes cook, cut chicken breasts into long 1/2-inch slices.

title: salsa
directions: Blend all ingredients along with juice in large pan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes.
Can in water bath for 10 minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix together Raisin Bran cereal, sugar, flour and salt. Add oil, eggs and buttermilk and mix well. Store in covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks. Bake in muffin tins at 375-400° for 15-20 minutes.

title: stuffed hamburgers
directions: Add milk to hamburger.
Divide into 10 patties.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each patty.
Seal up around stuffing.

title: deluxe chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired and spread into a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over cake, return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Using a knife dipped in water, spread the melted marshmallows evenly over cake.
Cool.

title: dirty rice
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Add soup mix, rice and water; let simmer until rice is done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until smooth.
Add sugar and coconut.
Mix well. Stir in vanilla.
Pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place small pats of margarine on top of pie filling. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken pot pie iii
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix soup and chicken. Mix milk, baking mix and egg. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into a ball.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill.

title: strawberry punch bowl dessert
directions: Cut angel food cake into squares.
Put into punch bowl and place pieces around the sides.
Take 1 large strawberry jello mix and prepare according to the directions on box.
Refrigerate until it begins to set.
Pour jello on top of the angel food cake.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours. Remove chicken from crock-pot; pour broth into Dutch oven or large pan and bring to boil. Make dumplings according to recipe on side of Bisquick box and cook in broth. While dumplings are cooking, pick meat off chicken bones. Serve dumplings over chicken.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes. Beat cream cheese with mixer until smooth. Add potatoes and remaining ingredients except paprika. Beat just until all combined. Spoon mixture into a lightly buttered 2 qt. casserole; sprinkle with paprika. Cover and store in refrigerator overnight. Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking. Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thorough heated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine in a 2-quart greased shallow baking dish, chicken, celery, rice, mayonnaise, water, lemon juice, onion, salt, sliced water chestnuts, undiluted cream of chicken soup, sliced eggs and pepper.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° or 400° oven.
Pour melted butter, sliced almonds and potato chips over.
Sprinkle cheese over top 10 to 15 minutes before done.

title: mile-high key lime pie
directions: In bowl, sprinkle gelatin over 3 tablespoons juice; set aside. In pot, over medium high heat, bring milk and remaining juice to a boil. Remove from heat. In a medium bowl, whisk yolks together to blend. In thin, steady stream whisk 1/3 of milk mixture into yolks until combined. Over medium heat, cook mixture whisking, until thick enough to coat back of spoon, 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in zest, reserved gelatin mixture and if desired, add 3 to 5 drops green food coloring. Pour into bowl. Press plastic wrap against surface of custard; freeze or refrigerate until set, 2 to 4 hours. Beat cream with sugar until stiff. At medium speed beat custard until smooth; fold in 3 1/2 cups whipped cream. Set aside 2 cups filling; pour remaining into crust. Freeze pie and reserved filling 15 minutes. Top pie with reserved filling, mounding toward center. Spread or pipe remaining whipped cream over pie. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 10 serving.

title: caramels
directions: Boil all ingredients except 1 cup of cream which is added after boiling mixture for 30 minutes.
Add second cup of cream and boil until firm stage.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven. Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: low-fat microwave tex-mex turkey chili
directions: Combine onion, garlic and oil in 2-quart glass measure.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High 3 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring every minute.
Add chili powder and next 4 ingredients.
Stir well.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 6 to 9 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring every 3 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Microwave, uncovered, on High 6 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: o.b.'s buffalo wings(hot!)
directions: Fry drumettes according to package instructions.
While drumettes are frying, combine all other ingredients (except butter or margarine) into medium bowl and stir.
Add butter/margarine and heat in microwave until completely melted.
(May heat over medium heat until melted.)
Whisk sauce until smooth and consistent.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake 30 minutes at 350°, or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Form into small balls and roll in confectioners sugar.
Place in tightly covered container and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain artichokes and grease pan with juice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into small square cake pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: white house bean soup
directions: Clean and soak beans overnight.
Cover with water.
Add diced carrots, potatoes, onions and celery.
Add ham hocks.
Cook 2 hours.
Add thyme, salt and pepper.
Serve.

title: chili pie
directions: Spread corn chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour chili over chips.
Spread cheese over chili.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve hot.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: hearty apple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda, allspice, nutmeg, and salt with fork. Blend in eggs, salad oil, and vanilla. Fold in apples, raisins and pecans. The dough will be very stiff. Spread dough into greased and floured oblong pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes. 12 Servings.

title: barbecue turkey loaf
directions: Combine 1 cup stuffing mix, vegetables, water and butter.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine remaining stuffing mix, turkey, eggs and 1/4 cup of the barbecue sauce; mix well.
Spoon a third of the turkey mixture into baking dish (or microwave-safe dish) and shape into 8 x 4-inch rectangle.
Cover with half the cheese.
Spoon vegetable mixture in center.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Pat remaining turkey mixture over cheese and shape into a loaf.
Brush with remaining barbecue sauce.

title: mexican corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° oven until set.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Melt oleo; stir in cracker crumbs and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together cream cheese, milk and sugar and beat until real creamy.
Spread this mixture over cracker mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over top of cheese mix.
Cool this real good!
Whip cream and spread over top of nuts.
Spread 1 can of cherry pie filling over top of cream.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook the pasta shells until al dente.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Drain well.
Saute the sausage and ground beef until crumbly.
Drain and discard the fat.
In a large frying pan, saute the garlic and onion in the oil until transparent.
Add the spinach and cook until the liquid is evaporated.
Combine the sauteed meat and spinach mixture in a bowl.
Add the remaining ingredients except the tomato sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together very well.
Place 2 1/2 cups of the tomato sauce into one 10 x 14-inch glass baking dish.
Fill the shells with the meat mixture; close them and place them seam side down in the sauce.
Top the shells with the remaining sauce and cover with Mozzarella and additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover the baking dish with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot throughout and bubbly.
Uncover the dish and broil a couple of minutes to brown the cheese slightly. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: chicken orleans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole.
Cover and microwave 40 to 45 minutes or bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream and mix well.
Serve with chips.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in hot greased pan at 350° until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie (lighter than libby's)
directions: Unfold pie crust, cut away and save outer 1/2 inch.
Roll crust between wax paper, fit in pan; hold pan up to the light to be sure there are no holes.
Patch holes with saved crust, if necessary; just pat a little strip on hole.
Crimp edge.
Put saved crust in freezer bag.
(After 3 or 4 pies, you will have enough for another pie.)
Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar and spices in small bowl and set aside.
Beat eggs; stir in pumpkin and sugar-spice mixture. Gradually add milk.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce temperature to 350°; bake for 30-40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack; serve immediately or refrigerate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat egg whites slightly and stir in other ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Melt margarine in microwave.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
(This pie is similar to a pecan pie.)

title: rice bread(1859 recipe)
directions: Boil the rice in water until it is quite tender; pour off the water and put the rice, before it is cold, to the flour.
Mix well the whole into a smooth dough; let rise in a warm place and then form it into loaves and bake them in a 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours according to their size.
If the rice is boiled in milk instead of water, it makes very delicious bread or cakes.
When boiled in this manner, it may be mixed with the flour without straining the liquid from it.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Pour off excess grease.
Add sauces, water, paste, onion, mushrooms, oregano, garlic salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, parsley flakes, salt and pepper and grated Parmesan.
Cook noodles.
Place 1/2 of the noodles in a baking dish, then spread 1/2 cottage cheese filling, 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of meat sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: grandma's goulash
directions: Brown hamburger; salt, pepper and onion to your taste.
Drain grease.
Add stewed tomatoes and tomato soup.
Simmer while macaroni cooks.
Add cooked macaroni to meat mixture and serve. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Combine macaroni, corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onion.
Blend thoroughly.
Put into 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Cube bread.
Toss cubes in melted butter. Arrange bread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine the spinach, parsley and onion in blender, until well blended.
Remove from the blender and add mayonnaise.
Cut center out of the bread and cube (cubes to be used for dip).
This should be made one day in advance.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: Put shortening or bacon drippings in frying pan.
Add a lot of onions and saute.
Add parsley.
Dice potatoes into pan and add water.
Cook and stir until
potatoes are done.

title: bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Add honey and oil.
Blend flour and salt. Add to liquid mixture. Knead a few minutes and cover.
Allow to rise until double in size.
Punch down and place into oiled loaf pans.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Heat unpeeled potatoes in water until boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer for 20 to 30 minutes. Drain, peel and dice potatoes.
In skillet over medium heat, melt butter and cook onion until tender. Stir in sugar, salt, flour and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened and boiling.
Gently stir in potatoes.
Heat through.
Garnish with parsley.

title: olive nut sandwich spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and olive juice until smooth. Add olives and pecans; mix. Put in jar and refrigerate.
Keeps well. Serve on thin slices of toast.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients together.
Heat margarine and broth together until margarine is melted; pour half of stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour over this the chicken mixture. Spread evenly.
Pour broth and butter over this.
Beat milk and eggs together and add to this.
Place in refrigerator overnight. Spread mushroom soup on top.
Add rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: lefse
directions: This recipe is a combination of an old one from my aunt and one from the Decorah, Iowa Nordic Fest, held the last weekend in July. It includes a Lutefisk eating contest.

title: creamy cabbage casserole
directions: Spread cabbage evenly in a 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish. Season with pepper.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle bacon over tomatoes.
Saute onion in the 1 teaspoon of butter or bacon drippings until transparent; arrange over top of casserole.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put layer of hamburger in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups together and pour over hamburger.
Place frozen Tater Tots in rows over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf burgers
directions: Mix meat, eggs, tomato juice, stuffing mix, onion, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Press mix into 12 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into 3-inch square.
Let set up in refrigerator for several hours. Bake in 375° oven until done.
Can be cooked on grill.
Top with cheese if desired.
Makes 12 burgers.

title: layered salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, layer lettuce, celery, mushrooms, eggs (sliced), green pepper, onion and peas (in order given).
Spread mayonnaise over top of salad; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover well and let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: red cabbage and apples
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely.
Melt butter; add cabbage, onion, seasonings and vinegar.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Add apples; cover and cook another 20 minutes or until tender, stirring every few minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Mix beef, onion, pizza, catsup, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and egg.
Shape into 9-inch round patty on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pour off fat.
Arrange cheese and olives on top. Make crisscross pattern with additional pizza catsup.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage. Add peppers, onions and celery; saute. Cook grits in water with salt. Combine cooked grits with sausage, peppers, onions and celery.
Pour mixture into 2-quart buttered casserole. Spread soup on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, butter and salt.
Mix with a fork.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs.
Mix with fork.
Then mix with hands on a floured surface.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with pizza cutter in long strips, then into thirds.
Bring ham, chicken, beef or turkey broth to a hard boil.
Drop noodles, one at a time, for 20 minutes.
Have plenty of broth.

title: old fashion pot-pie
directions: Roll out and cut into 2-inch squares; drop into boiling broth. Cook 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; let stand until yeast bubbles.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together; let rise, covered, in plastic until doubled in bulk.
Roll to a thickness of 1/2 inch.
Brush with melted butter.
Cover with mixture of cinnamon and sugar; roll and cut.
Put on greased baking sheet. Let rise and bake.
Brush with syrup (1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar) as soon as removed from oven.
Frost with glaze.

title: hamburger pizza casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Mix everything together, except cheese.
Pour in baking dish in sections.
Sprinkle cheese in between and on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini "apple" pie
directions: Cook zucchini with lemon juice and salt until tender-crisp. Mix dry ingredients together; add zucchini and mix well.
(It will be running.
"It's okay.")
Dump the filling into a 9-inch crust and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Mix raisins and 1/4 cup water in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Let stand until raisins are plump. Combine flour and next 5 ingredients in bowl. Cut in shortening until crumbly. Drain raisins, reserving liquid. Stir mixture of reserved liquid and buttermilk into flour mixture. Mix until smooth. Stir in raisins. Roll 1/2-inch thick on floured surface. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 425 degrees for 12 minutes. Combine confectioners' sugar, milk and vanilla in bowl. Mix well. Mix in water to make desired thickness. Drizzle over hot biscuits. Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Combine soup, mushrooms, chicken and mayonnaise.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Mix with macaroni and put into casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute chopped onions in shortening.
Cut meat in strips, then cube.
Remove onions.
Roll meat in flour and fry until brown.
Add onion, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add mushrooms, soup and sour cream.
Simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter, sour cream and eggs.
Add baking soda and flour.
Work
dough until ball forms.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Decorate with sugar sprinkles before baking.

title: shelley's candy
directions: Stir butter and sugar together over medium heat until it turns the color of caramel.
Get large Hershey bars (at least 8 ounces). Break up one on cookie sheet and put in oven at low temperature (about 150°) until it melts.
When candy is cooked, pour over melted Hershey bar and then put other Hershey bar over the hot candy.

title: tomato and dumplings
directions: Blend together milk and Bisquick (makes 8 dumplings).
Cook tomatoes and water until bubbly.
Drop dumplings by spoonful onto tomatoes.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes, then covered for 10 minutes. Serves 4.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water. Drain again.
Combine macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Toss lightly.
Chill.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Add salt to boiling water.
Stir in the meal, let cool until you can handle it; shape into patties and brown in skillet with at least 1 inch deep.
Cook until golden brown, drain on paper towel. Serve hot.
Delicious with turnip greens.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion, then drain. Mix taco seasoning, Ranch dressing and water to meat. Simmer until water cooks down. Add rest of ingredients and warm.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: microwave breakfast ring
directions: Put nuts in bottom of small microwave Bundt pan.
Mix together cinnamon and brown sugar.
Dip each biscuit in maple syrup and then in sugar mixture.
Arrange in pan sideways.
Microwave at power level 4, Medium, for 9 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: orange fluff
directions: Put one to two scoops of vanilla ice cream in a large glass. Fill with orange juice (the kind without pulp).
Enjoy.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake at 350° until done.
While the cake cools, mix 1 small package small Jell-O with 1 cup hot water. Cut slits in cake and pour the Jell-O over it.
Cool for 2 hours.

title: old fashioned raisin bars
directions: Combine raisins and water in a saucepan.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat, stir in oil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat into raisin mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Dust with confectioners sugar or frost.
Makes 2 dozen bars.

title: 30-minute caramel icing
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix well sugar, syrup and milk. Bring this to a boil on medium to high heat.
When it reaches first boiling, turn to simmer and cook 30 minutes.
Do not stir while cooking.
Cool and whip to desired consistency.

title: corn fritters
directions: Blend
together the flour, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix eggs, corn, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat until mixture is	smooth.
Drop by spoonful into deep hot shortening until brown.

title: summer coolness
directions: In a bowl, blend flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: peking roast
directions: With a sharp knife, cut slits in roast and insert slivers of onions and garlic. Place roast in a large bowl; pour 1 cup vinegar over roast and add enough water to cover. Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then lower oven to 300° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix eggs and sugar until smooth with mixer, then add milk and mix again.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Heat until warm.
Cool in refrigerator until cool, then freeze.

title: tuna pie
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes at 375°.
Toss together tuna, cheese and onion in bowl.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise and milk in another bowl and then add to the tuna mixture.
Spoon into baked pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Knife inserted in pie should come out clean when done.

title: cheese cake cupcakes(yields 24)
directions: Will need cupcake papers.

title: dijon chicken breasts
directions: In a medium glass bowl mix all ingredients except chicken breasts.
Spread mixture over chicken breasts from both sides. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
In a frying pan heat 2 Tbsp oil and bake the chicken for about 3 minutes per side or until done.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: decadent pie
directions: Cook and stir brown sugar and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and chocolate; stir until just melted.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Stir in coconut and pecans. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted 1 inch from center comes out clean.
Cool on rack. Combine whipped topping and bourbon.
Serve with pie.
Makes 1 pie.

title: reese's cups
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, powdered sugar and melted margarine.
Mix thoroughly and roll into patties.
Melt paraffin with chocolate chips.
Put 1 teaspoon of chocolate in the bottom of a cup, cake paper or a custard cup.
Put in 1 patty and add 1 teaspoon chocolate to cover patty.
Continue this process until all patties have been covered with chocolate.

title: playground's pecan pie
directions: Add remaining ingredients to eggs.
