Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate sauce
directions: Combine sugar and salt.
Melt chocolate and butter over medium heat.
Add sugar and evaporated milk; mix thoroughly.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Heat when serving.

title: copper pennies
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender; cool.
Alternate onion, pepper and carrots in layers.
Meanwhile, combine remainder of ingredients.
Beat until blended well.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate until serving.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: coconut praline dream pie
directions: Heat pecans, margarine and brown sugar in saucepan until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil exactly 30 seconds.
Spread in bottom of pie shell.
Cool.
Beat Dream Whip, 1 cup milk and vanilla in large bowl on low about 6 minutes, or until topping thickens and forms peaks.
Add remaining milk and pudding mixes. Blend on low speed.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in 1 cup coconut.
Spoon into pie shell. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Garnish with remaining coconut.

title: classic milk chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, and vanilla with electric mixer until creamy. Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely.
About 5 dozen cookies.

title: quick skillet dinner
directions: Brown meat and onions in shortening.
Drain off any excess fat and stir in water and next 5 ingredients.
Add macaroni; mix well. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes until macaroni is done.

title: sesame rainbow trout(this recipe is done over the grill.)
directions: Season inside of fish.
Combine oil, sesame seed, lemon juice, 1 teaspoon of salt and a dash of pepper; mix well.
Place fish in a well-greased, hinged wire basket.
Brush fish inside and out with sauce; close basket.
Cook over medium hot coals for 5 to 8 minutes.
Repeat brushing.
Turn; cook 5 to 8 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: candy pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a pizza pan.
Beat together first 7 ingredients.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in pizza pan and bake 20 minutes.
While hot sprinkle 1 cup chocolate chips over crust; drop peanut butter by spoonfuls over chips.
Let stand until chips are soft, then spread evenly over crust.
Decorate pizza with candy toppings.
Press in lightly.

title: queens chocolate apple flip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: quick barbecue beef bake
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 25 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator, then add 1 medium size tub Cool Whip.
Freeze in square freezable container.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate with margarine.
Fill 2/3 full of sliced apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
In separate bowl, mix sugar with melted butter and pecans. Add flour, egg and salt.
Mix well. Spread over the apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 65 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef teriyaki kabobs
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across the grain into long strips 1/8 inch thick.
For marinade, combine soy sauce, sherry, molasses, mustard, ginger root, garlic and 1/3 cup water. Pour over meat.
Marinate for 15 minutes at room temperature.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package instructions.
Drain and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Melt cheese and 1/2 stick of butter and pour over broccoli.
Melt remaining butter with cracker crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: leona's date cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spray cookie sheet with cooking spray. Scoop out mix with teaspoon. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen california vegetables(recipe for heart, diet, low-fat)
directions: Thaw vegetables and cook in boiling water about 10 minutes; drain, in large bowl.
Combine all ingredients except crackers and oleo, put in baking dish, cover with crackers, cut up oleo on top of crackers.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: lorraine's english pizza
directions: Grind cheese, pepper, bacon and onion in meat grinder (medium). Add mayonnaise, mustard, garlic or oregano and mix well.
Spread on English muffin halves.
Brown under broiler 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 to 15 muffin halves.

title: chili-frank burritos
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil and heat in a 375° oven for 5 minutes. On top of each tortilla, arrange one slice process cheese spread and one frankfurter.
Fold in ends of tortillas.
Roll up tortillas around process cheese spread and frankfurters.
Wrap in foil.
Bake in 375° oven about 15 minutes or until warm.
Makes 4 servings.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Crush enough wafers to cover and make crust in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add margarine; mix well.
Pat into dish.
Bake at 350° until crust is set.

title: banana split cake dessert
directions: Many layer dessert; assemble as follows!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish which has been greased with butter.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pat hamburger meat into 2-inch patties and brown.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put cream of mushroom and water in saucepan. Add drained green beans.
Heat for about 3 to 5 minutes on stove. Pour over hamburger patties and cook about 15 minutes in oven. Serve hot or cold.

title: hot jam sandwiches
directions: Cream butter until soft and fluffy.
Mix with coconut.
Blend apricot jam with cinnamon.
Make 4 sandwiches from raisin bread and jam.
Spread both sides of each sandwich with coconut-butter mixture.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl; mix well. Stuff turkey lightly or put in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: soy base
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
This may be frozen or refrigerated until needed.

title: sesame cheese wafers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toast sesame seeds in pie pan in oven for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring once to brown evenly.
In small bowl, cream together cheese spread and margarine.
Add flour, paprika and sesame seed.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into a 6-inch long roll.
Wrap in foil; refrigerate.
When ready to bake, heat oven to 400°. Slice roll into 1/4-inch wafers.
Bake on ungreased baking pan 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove from pan.
Makes six 4-wafer servings.
Contains 157 calories, 9 grams fat per serving.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper in saucepan and bring to boil whisking constantly so eggs blend well. Cook until thick, just 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over potatoes and sprinkle with parsley, bacon and paprika.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onions, raisins and bacon.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Toss all salad ingredients in a large bowl; pour dressing over and toss again when ready to serve.

title: banana whip
directions: Beat together egg whites and banana.
Gradually add sugar and beat, beat, beat, beat, beat until the mixture is no longer grainy from the sugar.
Consistency will be rather stiff.

title: angel bars
directions: Cover a 9 x 13-inch pan in graham crackers.
Combine butter, sugar, milk and egg in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until this is boiling.
Add coconut, nuts and crumbs; cook until thickens.
Pour over graham crackers in pan, then add another layer of crackers on top of the mixture.
Spread a can of sour cream or vanilla icing, heated, in a thin layer on top of crackers.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: light icebox cake
directions: Combine water, egg whites and cake mix.
Beat on low for 30 seconds, then medium for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: quiche italiano
directions: Do not prick unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes, weighted down.
Cook pepperoni, pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in spices.
In pastry shell, layer 1 cup Mozzarella, top with pepperoni mix.
In a bowl, mix eggs and milk and beat with fork until mixed.
Pour over pepperoni mix.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Top with tomato wedges, sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.
Bake 2 more minutes until cheese melts.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown turkey;
add beans and 1/2 cup salsa.
Spread 1/4 cup salsa in a	10-inch
pie plate; top with 3 tortillas.
Top with 1/2 the
meat
mixture, yogurt and cheese.	Repeat layers and cover with foil.
Bake
at	350° for 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: hamburger bean bake
directions: Combine meat, beans, soup, onion, Worcestershire sauce, oregano and salt.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine potatoes, egg and cheese.
Swirl around outer edge of casserole. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes, or until potatoes are lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Put 1 vanilla wafer in lined cake tins, round side up.
Mix rest of ingredients well.
Spoon mixture into cupcake tins, 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 22 to 24 cupcakes.
When cool, top with pie filling.

title: stuffed yellow squash with spinach
directions: Clean whole yellow squash and cook in boiling, salted water for about 3 to 4 minutes, just until rawness is gone.
Cool.

Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds and leave shells intact. When squash are cooked and ready as shells, mix spinach, Parmesan cheese, egg, thyme, garlic salt, bread crumbs, onions, butter, hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Stuff shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes and serve.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream, and mayonnaise; set aside.
Place half of crumbled cornbread into a large serving bowl. Layer half of beans, tomatoes, bell pepper, green onions, cheese, bacon and corn over cornbread.
Top with half of sour cream mixture. Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Garnish, if desired. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Yield:
10 to 12 side dish servings or 8 main-dish servings.

title: consomme rice
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients lightly in pan.
Add salt, consomme, water and cumin seed.
Let come to a boil; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Can be reheated.
Serves 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly, except the catsup.
Pack firmly into a greased loaf pan. Make dents in top of meat loaf. Pour the catsup over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cayman custard cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Put aside.
Melt butter; beat well with eggs.
Mix in sugar, water, milk and rest of the ingredients.
Blend with dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°. Custard should be lightly brown and will set as it cools.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and make balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butter pecan brownies
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well, then press into a 9 x 13 cake pan. Mix the next 4 ingredients with mixer, then pour on the top of pressed cake mixture. Sprinkle chopped pecans on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy chocolate dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer graham cracker and chocolate pudding (made as directed on box) in about 4 layers, ending with chocolate pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips for decoration, if desired.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Heat chocolate with water in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick, well blended and very smooth. Add sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and cool.
Store in refrigerator in tightly covered jar.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pork chops with scalloped potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Layer potatoes and onion in 1-quart casserole dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place pork chops on top.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over chops.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: garlic-sauted tomatoes
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over low heat.
Add garlic, basil and tomatoes and saut over low-medium heat until just wilted, maybe about 2 1/2 minutes. Add Asiago and serve hot with grill chicken or pork chops.

title: ziti salmon salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes ziti according to package directions; drain.
In a large bowl, combine ziti and remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: irene's spareribs
directions: Pour over about 2 pounds of spareribs and bake until tender.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients thoroughly.
Drop from a teaspoon on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Dissolve soda into buttermilk.
In large bowl, cream butter and sugar by hand.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add alternately flour, then buttermilk mixture, mixing well after each addition. (Alternate each three times.)
In another bowl, mix together the dates, orange slices, coconut, walnuts and pecans, then add to dough mixture and blend together.
Pour into tube pan and bake for 3 hours at 250°.
As soon as cake is removed from oven, pour mixture of orange juice (fresh or canned) and confectioners sugar over hot cake.
Let set overnight.

title: breakfast drink
directions: Blend in blender until frothy.
Serve in tall glasses.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Diamond walnuts, black walnuts or pecans are all good to use; whichever you prefer.
Yields 1 pound.

title: never fail chocolate frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Stir until sugar dissolves over moderate heat.
Then when mixture comes to rapid boil, boil exactly 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool and beat to consistency.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Dice chicken into small cubes. Chop onion and celery very fine. Saute all in olive oil until chicken is cooked. Transfer into a large pot - 5 qt. or larger. Add cooked rice and the remaining ingredients.
Simmer till rice has expanded.
Add salt and pepper to taste and more water as needed.
Left over soup will thicken.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then add crushed bananas and nuts.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Cook sausage until done, breaking into crumbles and stirring well.
Drain and set aside.
In the same skillet, scramble eggs until just set.
Keep warm.
Working quickly, place 1 cheese slice, 2 tablespoons cooked sausage and 2 to 4 tablespoons cooked eggs onto center of large tortilla.
Fold up 1-inch across bottom edge, then wrap right side over left, rolling into burrito shape. Serves 3 to 6.
Can be wrapped and stored in refrigerator overnight.
Reheat in microwave.

title: mammoms' ladyfinger cookies
directions: Cream butter; add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Chill and shape into "fingers."
Bake at 325° until brown.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar if desired.

title: salad dressing
directions: Combine the garlic, honey, mustard and vinegar and mix well with a hand whisk. Slowly drizzle extra virgin olive oil in a thin stream into the mixture while mixing with a hand whisk.

title: diabetic pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

With electric mixer, combine margarine, apple juice concentrate, fructose and mashed banana. Beat in egg. Stir dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture. Add raisins and nuts. Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable coating.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until firm in center.
Yields 20 servings. Each serving contains 142 calories (44% from fat).

title: cantaloupe brownies(nice and moist)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grate cantaloupe in blender or food processor to make 2 cups with the consistency of applesauce. Combine in a bowl the dry ingredients.
Add wet ingredients and nuts; stir just to combine.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 12 large brownies.

title: wanda's pea salad
directions: Stir all except peas with Miracle Whip.
Add peas last, folding gently.

title: dirt cake
directions: Finely crush all cookies.

title: applesauce drop doughnuts
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil, frying until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.

title: london broil
directions: Marinate steak 1 hour in steak sauce, lemon juice, onion, and garlic.
Preheat grill.
Remove steak from marinade, season with salt and pepper.
Grill over medium heat.
Grill to desired doneness (10 - 15 minutes for medium well) basting often and turning only once.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour, salt, baking powder and sugar together. (If using self-rising cornmeal mix, omit salt and baking powder.)

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop the cabbage and onion.
Cook in boiling water (to cover) until almost tender; drain.
Grate the cheese and add to cabbage and onion.
Whip together the egg and evaporated milk.
Add to cabbage, onion and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Grease a 2-quart casserole dish with a stick of margarine; save the remainder.
Pour cabbage mixture into a greased dish; dot top with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat milk and pudding until it gets thick; blend in Cool Whip. Add bananas and vanilla wafers.
Mix all together.

title: light and zesty chicken 'n rice
directions: *One 2 pound cut up chicken may be substituted.

title: country style spareribs
directions: Boil ribs in salted water for 45 to 60 minutes.
Drain.
Place ribs in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Saute onion in oleo; stir in remaining ingredients and cook until heated.
Pour over ribs and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or longer.

title: cream cheese kittles
directions: Knead first 6 ingredients together.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Chill overnight.
Mix nut stuffing with sugar.

title: lemon-raisin scones
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat inside of 12 medium-sized muffin cups with nonstick vegetable oil cooking spray.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and rind in large bowl. Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add raisins.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a large pot, cook onions in fat until golden.
Add tomato, pepper, paprika, beef, tomato paste and salt.
Cook, stirring over medium heat, until beef loses its redness.
Reduce heat; add water. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat.
Strain gravy, then return to pan with meat.
Add potatoes and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Mix all together and put 1/2 in a Pyrex pan.
Let set.
Spread 8 ounces sour cream on top of set jello.
Pour other 1/2 of jello on top.
Let set and cut into squares.

title: chicken curry
directions: The day before, cook the chicken in 3 1/2 cups of water until the bones can be removed, then pressure cook the pieces. Refrigerate meat and broth about 30 minutes.
Before serving, heat chicken in double boiler.
Cook rice per label.
Melt butter and stir in all spices.
Add broth and heavy cream.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Add applesauce and cook about 5 minutes.
Add more seasonings if needed.
Mix this with chicken and heat 20 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: maine baked soldier beans
directions: Pick beans over for any possible pebbles.,
Soak the beans overnight in water that covers the beans by at least three inches. They swell, thus the need for ample water.
In the morning drain the beans and again cover with water.
Now parboil hem until they just begin to soften.
When you remove a spoonful and blow on them, the skins should split and roll back.
At this point, add 1 Tbsp. of baking soda and let it foam up.
Now drain the beans into a colander and rinse.

title: swedish gingersnaps
directions: Sift together flour, spices, salt, baking powder, baking soda and cocoa and set aside.
Combine butter, molasses and brown sugar in a mixing bowl and beat until lightened and smooth.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is well blended and smooth.
Wrap dough in waxed paper and refrigerate at least 1 1/2 hours or up to 24 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°. Working with half of the dough at a time, and keeping the remaining dough refrigerated, shape dough into 1-inch balls and place 1 1/2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Lightly grease the bottom of a flat-bottomed drinking glass and dip into granulated sugar.
Flatten each ball to about 1/4-inch thick, dipping glass frequently to keep from sticking.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, just until tinged brown at the edges.
Place on wire racks to cool.
Store airtight up to 2 weeks.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven
Grease loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x
x
1/2-inch) with shortening.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and
eggs
in
a
large bowl with a wooden spoon. Stir in remaining
ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake until a wooden pick inserted
in
center
comes
out
clean, 60 to 70 minutes.	Let cool 10 minutes, then loosen sides of loaf from pan and
remove from pan.
Let cool completely before slicing. Makes 1 loaf.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Heat oven to moderate, 375°. Sift together flour, soda and salt; set aside. Blend butter, sugars, vanilla and water. Beat in egg. Add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in oats and chocolate morsels or coconut. Drop by rounded 1/2 teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 45 cookies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and quarter.
Mix well and freeze.

title: scout night meal
directions: Brown ground beef
and	drain.	Add
to
ground beef in large skillet,
sliced
potatoes,
chopped
onion,
salt	and pepper. Add water to
cover.
Bring to boil; cover and simmer until done. If your guys are late, it's still good...

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in water.
Remove from heat and stir in stuffing mix.
Add egg; mix in raw sausage.
Chill. Shape into oblong balls, about the size of a walnut.
Wrap with bacon strips.
Cook on rack in 400° oven until bacon is done, turning once.

title: baked asparagus
directions: Layer asparagus in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour margarine or butter and oil over asparagus.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball, about 30 minutes.
Put in peanut butter, marshmallow whip and vanilla and beat until stiff.
Spread in a 9 inch x 11 inch greased pan. Cut when set.
For chocolate fudge, use 2/3 c. cocoa.

title: ham n' cheese roll-ups
directions: Blend cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, chives/parsley and powdered mustard.
Spread over ham; roll up like jelly roll. Cover and chill 2 hours.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place on bread.
Yields 25 to 30.

title: frozen banana crunch
directions: Mix the sugar and water until the sugar is dissolved.
Add the bananas, pineapple juice, orange juice concentrate and lemonade to the sugar water.
Freeze.
Makes 2 gallons of frozen concentrate. To serve, thaw partially and add ginger ale or Sprite.

title: creamy cheese spinach potato casserole
directions: In microwavable casserole, cook spinach in 1 cup of water on High for 8 minutes; rotate 1/2 way with lid.
Add cheese, garlic powder, margarine, pepper, milk and instant potatoes.
Mix well. Microwave on High (3 intervals) at 1 minute and 45 seconds; rotate and mix each.

title: foil dinner
directions: Prepare four squares of doubled heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 450° for 50 minutes or cook over coals, turning once.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.

title: puppy chow(snack food)
directions: Heat oleo, peanut butter and chips together until melted. Pour over cereal and stir until well coated.
Mix in confectioners sugar; stir to coat.
Serve immediately.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: italian bean soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat in oil, saute celery, carrots, onion, zucchini and pepper until vegetables are tender and begin to brown, about 15 minutes.
Stir in stewed tomatoes, chicken broth, chopped spinach, white beans and 2 cups water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Spoon soup into large soup bowls. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: cavatelli con broccoli
directions: Steam or boil broccoli until tender, not soft.
Heat oil; lightly saute garlic and shallots or scallions until golden.
Add chopped tomatoes and continue to saute.
Add chicken stock and spices.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook cavatelli. Drain.
Add cooked broccoli to chicken stock mixture.
Pour over cavatelli.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves 5.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, flour, salt and sugar.
Add beaten eggs with milk and margarine.
Turn into greased souffle dish or casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring 3 or 4 times in early stages of baking before mixture sets.
Do not stir once mixture has set.
Continue to bake until golden and puffy.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Skin chicken; sprinkle garlic and onion salt on chicken.
Mix together preserves, dressing, pineapple and onion soup.
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish, pour mixture over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then top with green pepper and onion.
Bake about 15 minutes longer, or until chicken is tender.

title: lemon cake dessert
directions: Into large bowl of your electric mixer put gelatin, granulated sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, salad oil and water. Beat at slow speed until ingredients are combined. Then beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13
inch baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: no weep meringue
directions: Slowly cook until clear the granulated sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites to froth stage. Add the 6 level tablespoons of powdered sugar, 1 at a time, beating after each one.
When eggs are light and form a fold over wet peak, beat in the cooked mixture.
Be very careful to seal the meringue well to the pie crust when applying.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until nicely browned.
Cool slowly out of drafts.

title: warm brownie pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and 1/3 cup cocoa in medium bowl.
Combine milk, margarine and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until blended.
Spoon batter evenly into prepared pan.
Combine brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa in small bowl.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to oatmeal mixture.
Beat well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix egg, sugar, flour, pineapple juice and vinegar in small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Cool this mixture. Mix diced apples, Cool Whip, peanuts and pineapple.
Add cooled mixture.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: polish beet soup
directions: Drain beet juice into a glass and add 2 tablespoons vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut beets in thin strips and place in a bowl with 3 tablespoons vinegar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.

title: easy pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put 2 cups of batter in another bowl and mix with 1/2 package of instant chocolate pudding.
Pour half of pistachio mixture into greased and floured Bundt pan, then do the same with the chocolate mixture, then the rest of the pistachio mixture.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: "o's" cheese surprise
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Heat cheeses in oven or microwave. Add sausage and jalapenos (seeded and chopped) with some of their juice.
Can be served warm with crackers or chill and slice to serve on crackers or Melba toast.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Place lamb in large roaster.
Rub lamb with minced garlic. Generously season entire roast with salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion powder.
Place bouillon cubes in hot water, stir to dissolve.
Pour into bottom of roaster.
Cover and place in preheated 325° oven for 6 to 6 1/2 hours, until outside is nicely browned.
Can make a gravy by removing roast from pan, setting aside. Bring drippings to a boil on top of stove.
Mix about 2 tablespoons cornstarch with enough water to make a thin mixture. Stir into boiling drippings, turn to medium-low heat, mixing until thickened slightly.

title: punch
directions: Mix and freeze, then when ready to serve thaw and add 2 quarts Canadian
ginger
ale and 1 quart club soda.
Float ice cream or sherbet on top.

title: joanne's sugar coated pecans
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Mix all ingredients except nuts together.
Dip nuts into mixture and place on sheet.
Bake in 250° oven for 30 minutes.

title: low-sugar apple pie
directions: Pare apples and slice thin; add apple juice, sugar and NutraSweet, mixed with salt and spices.
Fill 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix orange Jell-O and water and let cool.
Mix in all other ingredients well and chill.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, salt, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool before removing from baking sheet.

title: macaroon torte
directions: Boil 1/2 of the pineapple juice.
Add Knox gelatine until thick.
Line a 9 x 11-inch glass pan with cookies standing along sides, crushed on bottom (save some crushed cookies for top).

title: house of spitz flecked white pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, frosting mix, eggs, sour cream and water. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Add grated chocolate and pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 20 minutes.

title: creamy beef rotini
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with the onion; sprinkle with garlic powder to taste.
Add cream of mushroom soup, Miracle Whip and the milk to ground beef in skillet.
Simmer on medium to low heat until heated through.
Cook rotini using directions on bag or box; drain rotini and mix with creamy beef sauce.
Serve hot with your favorite vegetable or side dish.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Knead with hand in a small bowl graham cracker crumbs, ground walnuts, 4 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons sugar until blended.
Press crumb mixture onto bottom and half way up side of a 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter until smooth.
Add orange peel, almond extract, eggs and 1/2 cup sugar; beat until well blended, occasionally scraping bowl with a rubber spatula.
Fold in chocolate pieces.
Spoon into pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool and cover; refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
To serve, carefully remove side of pan from cheese cake.
Serves about 16 (approximately 380 calories).

title: ribbon jello
directions: Bring to boil 2 cups milk and 1 cup sugar.
Cool.
Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup water.
Put into warm milk and sugar. Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Cool and stir in 2 cups sour cream and vanilla.
Beat until creamy; set aside.
Mix jello, one box at a time.
Use 1 3/4 cups boiling water to each box.
Pour first box, after dissolved, into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Chill. When set, pout 1/4 of sour cream mixture and spread evenly.
Then prepare second box of jello and repeat until all is used.

title: tuna pie(microwave)
directions: Cook rice.
In 9-inch pie plate melt 1/2 cup oleo.
Add tuna, thyme and bread crumbs. Mix well and press out in bottom and sides of pie plate.
Mix together eggs, rice and onions.
Spoon into tuna-lined pie plate.
Cover with wax paper and cook 9 to 11 minutes, rotating 1/2 turn after 5 minutes. Garnish with tomato slices.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cool and add vanilla.

title: glazed pork roast
directions: Start coals in outdoor grill.
Place bratwurst in a large saucepan; cover bratwurst with beer.
Add onion rings from one onion and add just enough water to cover bratwurst and onion, if necessary.
Bring beer to a simmer and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Stir in milk to make soft dough.
Knead lightly; pat out about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out and place one biscuit on top of another.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: creole jambalaya
directions: Combine meat, rice and tomatoes.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Add green peppers, celery and onions.
Pour mixture into baking dish. Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Better if served hot.)

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Mix and press into pan with hands. Add pecans on top of cake. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Microwave chips until melted, then add other ingredients. Stays warm for about 1 hour.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Use large skillet or wok.
Fry chicken strips in oil over medium heat until chicken is opaque.
Add pepper, onion, garlic and carrots; stir-fry until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Combine honey, soy sauce, cornstarch, ginger and cayenne.
Add to chicken mixture.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture thickens and glaze develops.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Stir until well blended. Serve over rice.
Serves 5.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Heat oil, brown chicken on all sides.
(Take out chicken.) Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat, add chicken.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.

title: apple delight
directions: Mix oleo and flour until crumbly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Peel apples and slice on crust; top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy does-it donuts
directions: In medium bowl beat eggs; set aside.
Drain both cans of apples or blueberries from muffin mixes; add to beaten eggs. Stir in flour and dry muffin mixes.
On a well-floured board roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out donuts with floured 2 1/2-inch donut cutter, pressing straight down.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix well the shortening, brown sugar, eggs and buttermilk. Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix in pecans, dates and cherries.
Chill dough for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie with pecan half or half cherry.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°. If you use self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: pineapple-nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, mix well flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder, salt, baking soda, and ground mace.
In small bowl, beat egg, crushed pineapple with its liquid, milk and margarine.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Pour the batter into greased pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan on wire rack ten minutes. Remove bread from pan.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar, beat until smooth.
Add hot water and egg yolks then beat well.
Sift together and add dry ingredients. Stir in potatoes, nuts and vanilla; beat well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake in three greased cake pans for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cook fish in a 3-quart saucepan in water, until fish flakes easily.
Brown salt pork in skillet; remove from skillet.
Saute onions in drippings until golden.
Add onions and salt pork to saucepan.
Add potatoes and water to cover.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add evaporated milk.
Heat to serving temperature. Yield:
6 servings.

title: custard pumpkin pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and cornstarch together.
Then add remaining ingredients and cook at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes or until set up.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 9 dumplings (oblong) and drop into boiling water.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Serve with roast pork and sauerkraut.
For best results, don't use new potatoes.

title: old-fashioned cabbage rolls
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend meats with egg, milk and bread crumbs. Stir in salt, molasses, ginger, nutmeg, allspice and onion; mix well.
Cut out core of cabbage.
Carefully separate outer 12 leaves (reserve remainder for other use).
Remove center thick vein of each leaf.
Drop leaves into boiling water.
Cover and steam 3 minutes or until soft and bright green.
Remove with slotted spoon; reserve liquid.
Evenly divide meat among cabbage leaves.
Fold sides in and roll up.
Fasten with wooden pick. Heat butter in frying pan.
Brown rolls on all sides.
Transfer them to a 3-quart casserole as they brown.

title: croutons
directions: Put bread on a cookie sheet and let "stale" in a warm oven, turning frequently, or you can leave bread out on countertop for about 5 hours and let "stale."
Melt butter.
Add garlic powder, salt and parsley.
Brush butter mixture on both sides of bread. Cut bread into cubes.
Bake at 325° until bread is toasty brown on bottom.
Turn bread over and brown on the other side.
Leftover croutons keep well in a Tupperware bowl.

title: sugar free sunshine punch
directions: Pour 7-up over sherbet in a big bowl and stir until partly thawed and foamy. Add the rest of the ingredients and serve immediately.

title: barbecue beef burgers
directions: Melt fat in a large fry pan.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes, until onions are transparent.
Add meat, stirring with a fork to separate and cook about 5 minutes until brown.
Blend in soup, water and seasoning. Simmer for 15 minutes longer, until meat is done.
Add corn. Simmer 5 minutes longer.
Serve over toasted buns.

title: chatters
directions: Let butter and cheese soften; mix with mayonnaise, garlic and seasoned salt.
Add crabmeat/shrimp.
Spread on split muffins. Freeze for 10 minutes; cut into eighths.
Broil until light brown.

title: lemon-chicken
directions: Broil chicken for about 30 minutes, until cooked well inside. Turn over occasionally.

title: shrimp jambalaya "or crawfish"
directions: Heat shortening; add flour and let it cook slowly until golden brown.
Stir constantly.
Add onions, peppers, garlic and celery. Cook slowly until transparent; stir often.
Then add tomatoes and let cook until oil rises to top.
Stir in raw rice, raw shrimp and 2 1/2 cups water.
Cook, covered, over low heat until rice is tender.
Add more oil and water if mixture appears to be dry.
Add minced parsley and onion tops.
Serve hot.

title: billy's spinach pies
directions: One loaf equals 4 pies.
Take dough out of freezer 4 hours before use.
Cook frozen spinach as directed on package.
Saute 1 small onion (chopped) and 1 clove garlic (chopped).
Add cooked, drained spinach and fry 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: scallops with vegetables
directions: Place mushrooms in bowl and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain.
Squeeze out excess water.
Cut into thin slices.
Rinse scallops and drain.
Trim, if necessary, and cut into quarters.
Peel yellow onions, cut into wedges and separate layers.
Cut celery into 1/2 inch diagonal slices.
Wash and trim green beans.
Cut beans into 1 inch diagonal slices.
Cut green onions into thin diagonal slices.
Heat oil in wok over high heat.
Add onions, celery, beans, ginger and garlic to oil. Stir-fry 3 minutes.
Measure cornstarch into small bowl.
Blend in a few tablespoons of the water and mix until smooth.
Stir in the remaining water, the sherry, soy sauce and bouillon.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture boils.
Add scallops, mushrooms, green onions and corn.
Cook and stir until scallops are tender, about 4 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hard tack
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Cook until hard crack (300°). Add flavoring and coloring.
Put on greased cookie sheet and cool until lukewarm. Cut into pieces with scissors.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Layer fruit and pie filling in a casserole dish in the order given.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together; sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Serve hot.
This is quick and easy and especially good for brunch on cool fall mornings.

title: jambalaya
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except shrimp in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: french toast
directions: Combine all ingredients well. Heat small amount of butter or oil in skillet. Dip slice of bread in egg mixture and brown in oil.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, rice and water over medium heat until blended. Pour in casserole.
Place chicken breasts on top of mixture.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done at 375°.
(May need to stir and add water approximately halfway through cooking time.)

title: sandies
directions: Heat oven to 325°. In a mixing bowl, beat butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add about half of the flour, the sugar, vanilla and 1 tablespoon water. Beat until thoroughly combined. Beat in remaining flour. Stir in pecans. Shape into 1-inch balls or 2 x 1/2-inch fingers or crescents. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 325° oven about 20 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned. Cool cookies on a wire rack. Gently shake cooled cookies in a bag with powdered sugar. Makes about 36.

title: sherried chicken breast
directions: Salt chicken breasts and place in single layer, skin side up, in a casserole.
Mix soup, sour cream, sherry and mushrooms.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake for 1/2 hour.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: In 2-quart pan, over high heat, bring first 4 ingredients to a boil (sugar, water, vinegar and celery seed).
Boil 1 minute. Cool to room temperature.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter.
Heat to boiling over medium heat.
Stir constantly as mixture reaches a soft ball stage, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until well blended.
Pour into an 8-inch square buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cranberry salad for thanksgiving(aunt helen's recipe)
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Add sugar to chopped fresh cranberries; then add oranges and nuts.
Combine with jello and refrigerate to congeal.

title: never fail christmas cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Beat eggs and mix with vanilla and lemon extract.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well. Shape dough into 2 balls.
Put in refrigerator.
Chill 24 hours. Cut each ball in half.
Roll out to 1/8-inch.
Cut out with Christmas cookie cutters; only take out one ball of cookie dough at a time.
Leave rest in refrigerator.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°. Do not brown.
Decorate and ice for Christmas.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease a pizza pan and spread cookie mix on it.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread on cookie mix.
Dip bananas in lemon juice to keep them from turning black.
Arrange fruit on top of cream cheese mixture, in a circle, one fruit at a time, working towards the center.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. In small bowl, blend mayonnaise, bread crumbs, cheese and garlic; fold in crabmeat. Evenly spoon mixture into mushroom caps. On baking sheet, arrange mushroom caps. Bake for 20 minutes or until heated through and lightly browned.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef until it is crumbled.
Drain off fat.
Stuff meat into noodles (do not cook noodles, they are easier to stuff). Layer in casserole
dish.
Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Feeds 4 people.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, turkey or chicken.
Add all cans and juices.
Add
taco seasoning.
Let simmer 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine graham crackers and margarine.
Press on bottom of pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Place dry ingredients in a 2 quart sauce pan and stir until completely mixed.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients 10 minutes or until apples are almost done.
Mix
tablespoons
margarine and brown sugar, cream. Mix
flour,
baking
powder
and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix
well.
Put
apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan
and
add topping.
Pat down lightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour standard cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes, then do a toothpick test.
If the brownies start to pull away from the sides of the pan, then they are done.

title: southern cornbread
directions: Blend with wire wisk in order given.
Use stoneground fresh cornmeal for best results.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dividing this recipe and using a smaller pan is acceptable.
Test for doneness same as for cakes.

title: coffee can butter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water containing the ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar.
After 15 minutes, add the remaining ingredients.
Put in 2 one pound coffee cans, well greased or one 2 pound coffee can.
Bake at 350° (2 cans for 45 minutes or 1 can for 60 minutes).

title: sandwich steak rolls
directions: Make stuffing as directed, one package for 4 rolls.
Wrap 2 steaks around 1 1/2 tablespoons stuffing.
Put as many as you want in baking dish.
Cover with soup.
Add a little water to rinse can.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
I cover for first 1/2 hour, then uncover for remainder.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom

title: bluefish cakes
directions: Put bluefish fillets in cold
water.
Bring
to boiling point, then simmer for
hour.
Drain	off water and cool. Break up fish in flakes, add saltines, beaten egg (or 2).
Mix until it feels
the	right
consistency.
Add salt, pepper and Old Bay seasoning to
taste.
Make	into
cakes and fry in hot oil.

title: cooked chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to boil and cook just one minute, stirring constantly.
Let cool and spread.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Saute onion in butter until yellow.
Combine with celery, salt, pepper, parsley, lemon juice and flaked salmon.
Combine eggs with milk and pour over bread crumbs.
Add to other ingredients and blend well.
Pack into well-greased loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and cut unpared tomatoes into slices about 1/3-inch thick. Beat eggs and milk. Dip tomatoes into flour, then egg mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs. Fry in skillet with hot oil until brown on both sides. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: nibblers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in covered container and shake occasionally over a 24 hour period.
Nibble (if you can).

title: strawberry salad supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix jello, boiling water and strawberries; gel slightly.
Mix pretzels, pecans, sugar and melted butter.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 10 minutes; cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Spoon jello mixture on top.
Chill well.

title: bible cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add other ingredients as usual for any other cake.
Fold egg whites in gradually.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: peel a pound soup
directions: Follow directions on soup mix.
Add vegetables and V-8 juice; cook until done.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.

title: life's recipe
directions: A preserving kettle is best.
If he sputters, do not be anxious; some husbands do this until they are quite done.
Add a little sugar in the form of kisses but no pepper or vinegar of any sort or account.
A little spice, if used with judgement, will improve him.
Do not stick any sharp instruments into him to see if he is done.
Stir him gently, lest he lie too close to the bottom of the kettle and becomes useless.

title: egg beater noodles
directions: Mix together.
Roll out, dry and cut as usual.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put into bowl the following:
ground beef, bread crumbs, chopped onion, catsup, egg, salt, black pepper and milk.
Mix well and shape into loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Pour sauce over this.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: In 8-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup, chicken, water, cumin and chilies.
Heat through.
Butter tortillas, wrap in foil and heat in 350° oven for approximately 10 minutes.
Spoon about 1/3 cup soup mixture onto each tortilla; roll up.
Arrange tortillas in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour taco sauce evenly over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, uncover, bake 5 more minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss first 4 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Pour over tossed ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add sugar; stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves, then add 3 tablespoons water and corn syrup.
Cook until 290°, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add coarse nuts.
Spread on buttered baking sheet.
Immediately sprinkle chocolate over top; let stand a few minutes, then spread evenly.
Sprinkle with fine nuts.
Chill until firm; break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into cake pan (9 x 9-inch ungreased) that cake is to be baked in.
Make 3 holes in dry ingredients.
Into the first hole, pour vanilla, in second hole, put vinegar and in third hole, put the melted butter.
Over all, pour cold water and mix well.
Clean sides and spoon often.
Stir until smooth.
Clean down sides and bake at 350° until done with clean toothpick test.
Do not remove from pan.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Pour into crust.
Layer banana slices and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with strawberries and nuts.
Chill until served.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix sugar, water, egg white, corn syrup and salt in top double boiler.
Beat about 1 minute to blend thoroughly.
Place over boiling water.
Beat constantly with electric mixer on high speed until it stands stiff peaks.
Remove from boiling water. Immediately pour into large bowl.
Add vanilla until thick enough to spread about 1 minute.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook ground pears, sugar and pineapple until it changes color and is thick.
Put into jars hot and seal.

title: barbecued meatballs(appetizer)
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, crumbs, 1/4 cup minced onions, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Press one cube of cheese into center of each meatball.
Cook meatballs in a large skillet, medium heat, until browned on all sides.
Drain well and set meatballs aside.

title: baked ham with peaches
directions: Preheat oven to 300° (baking schedule:
15 minutes per pound). Score fat in diamond pattern and stud with cloves.
If there is a skin or rind, roll it back for scoring and then back on for roasting.
It will be removed later.
Roast 1 hour on rack in preheated oven.
Remove ham from oven, remove rind, pour orange juice in baking pan and sprinkle grated orange zest over ham. Return to oven for another hour, basting every 15 minutes.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat
oven
Prepare	pie shell.
Mix sugars, flour, nutmeg
and
cinnamon.
Stir apples into this mixture. Pour into a
9-inch pastry lined pie plate.
Cover with a top crust that has
slits	cut in it; seal and crimp.
Bake until crust is
brown and juice bubbles through slit in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.	Time of preparation: 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade irish creme liqueur
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Serve over ice, if desired.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator up to 1 month.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil; beat well.
Add flour mixture; beat well.
Add pumpkin; mix and pour into pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Add chocolate chips or raisins as desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Spread sausage in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or smaller is better.
Sprinkle cubed bread over the sausage. Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour egg mixture over bread and sausage.
Top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: beer bread
directions: Combine flour and sugar in bowl.
Make a "well" in center and pour in a can of beer.
Mix well.
Put into greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Rub crust with stick of butter when done. Very good and tastes like you worked a lot harder on it than you did.

title: never fail divinity candy
directions: Beat egg whites stiffly.
Stir well the sugar, corn syrup and boiling water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until hard ball forms when a drop is placed in cold water.
Pour 2/3 of syrup mixture into egg whites, beating as poured.
Re-cook 1/3 of syrup for 1 minute.
Then pour into egg mixture and beat until thick and cooled.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into greased platter or drop onto waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: mildred's veggie casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix onion with Veg-All, Cheddar cheese soup, water chestnuts and mayo.
Pour all into casserole dish. Crush crackers and put cracker crumbs on top of mixture.
Drizzle 3/4 stick of butter (melted) over cracker crumbs.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: velveeta dip
directions: Fry ground round and sausage.
Drain grease.
Mix cheese, soup and milk.
Cook slowly in the crock-pot.
Add meat and cook until ready to eat (slowly).

title: quick lasagne
directions: In a large glass baking dish, layer the sauce, hamburger, noodles, Ricotta cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Layer until you have 2 layers of each.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Add the Mozzarella to the top and bake for 5 minutes more.
Let cool for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Combine mustard, molasses, vinegar, soy sauce, pineapple and brown sugar in dish; mix well. Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender, basting frequently.

title: intermezzo
directions: Combine sugar and water in large saucepan.
Bring to boiling. Cook, stirring often until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat. Stir in grapefruit juice.
Blend well.
Pour in large metal bowl; chill until very cold.
Pour mixture into Rubbermaid ice cream server.
Freeze.
Pack sorbet into 6-cup plastic server.
Store in freezer at least 2 hours.
To serve, scoop sorbet with tiny ice cream scoop into small stemmed glasses.
Spoon 1 tablespoon Galliano over each just before serving.
This is served between courses to clear palate.

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Thoroughly beat in egg and vanilla extract; then blend in sifted dry ingredients. Mix in chopped Baby Ruth candy bars.
Drop by half-teaspoonfuls, about 2 inches apart, onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets and place on wire racks to cool.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, gradually add sugar and blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread in cooled crust.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Serve with favorite pie filling.

title: pork fried rice(makes 6 servings)
directions: Combine egg, water and 1/8 teaspoon salt and beat.
Heat wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add 2 teaspoons oil and pour in egg mixture.
Tilt pan to coat surface.
Cook until pancake is set and bottom is slightly golden.
Turn and cool, then roll up tightly.
Slice crosswise into slivers; set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add water, eggs and pumpkin. Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 375°.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches, sliced, and mix with 3/4 cup sugar.
Make batter of remaining ingredients except butter.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour in batter and spoon peaches and sugar into the center. Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all
ingredients except Cool Whip.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake
at 350° until set.
Top with Cool Whip after it cools if desired.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts together until moist.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread on top of cooled crust.
Top with cherry pie filling and chill until ready to serve.

title: indiana cake
directions: *Can mix 1 cup milk with 1 teaspoon vinegar and set aside for 5 minutes.
This will equal 1 cup buttermilk.

title: cherry delights
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease sheets.
Cream butter and sugar. Stir in corn syrup, egg yolks and flour. Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in beaten egg whites and roll in chopped nuts.
Place on greased sheets.
Press candied cherry halves into centers. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cake cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the eggs, cake mix, oatmeal, chips or whatever you really like in your cookies.
The kids like the bright colors of the M&M's baking chips.
Mix by hand; this gets very thick.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; do not overbake.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut pineapple in 1-inch sections.
Take 1/2 slice bacon and roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes until bacon is brown.
Serve hot.
You may also use 1/2-inch pieces of cream cheese instead of pineapple.

title: cherry delight
directions: Melt butter; add crackers and 2 1/2 cups sugar; mix well. Line bottom of loaf pan.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar well. Fold into Dream Whip (mix according to directions).
Put cherries over crackers and whipped topping on top.
Chill before serving.

title: crab dip
directions: Slice bar of cream cheese the long way.
Lay them end to end or side by side on a dish.
Spread crabmeat over cream cheese. Pour cocktail sauce over crabmeat.
Great with crackers.

title: anise cookies(slices)
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Add baking powder and mix with almonds.
Add oil and extract.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour and mix, then add rest of flour.
Dough will be sticky.
Divide dough in half.
Put half on cookie sheet.
Shape into long oval.
Shape dough with palm of hand.
Add other half and do same beside it. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While hot, slice diagonally, 1 1/2- inches wide.
Turn on side and bake 15 minutes.

title: apricot bars(yummy!)
directions: Cook 3/4 cup sugar, 1/4 cup apricot juice and apricots until slightly thickened.
Cream together butter and 1 cup sugar.
Blend in flour and soda.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Place 3 cups of mixture (very dry) in bottom of greased 12 x 8-inch pan.
Pat down.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and spread apricot mixture over cooked portion.
Sprinkle remaining mixture on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or more until golden brown.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark. Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop on wax paper.

title: cheese noodles
directions: Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy, add crumbled Roquefort cheese together with chopped olives and onions.
Form into finger-length rolls and roll in Chinese noodles.
Serve with salad.

title: crab meat in patty shells
directions: Remove the stems from mushrooms.
Combine the stems with water in a saucepan and cook until tender; drain reserving the liquid and discard the stems.
Slice the mushrooms caps and cook in butter melted in a double boiler over hot water.
Cook for 3 minutes, stir in flour, sour cream, and the reserved mushroom liquid.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper, canned crab, and sherry; mix well.
Cook, covered for 5 minutes.
Form pie shell dough into individual serving cups in a miniature muffin tin and bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until browned.
Spoon the crab mixture into the shells and serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: baked carrots
directions: Saute sausage and onion.
Add flour, salt, dry mustard, celery salt, pepper and milk.
Cook until thick.

title: sweet and sour drumsticks
directions: Heat broiler.
Combine garlic, preserves, soya sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, ginger and red pepper flakes.
Put drumsticks on rack on broiler pan.
Brush with some of the soya sauce mixture.
Broil about 6 inches from source of heat, turning and brushing occasionally with soya sauce mixture until done, about 20 minutes.

title: chicken manicotti with chive cream sauce
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to directions and drain. Rinse with cold water.
Drain again.

title: goulash(60 people)
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook peppers and onions.
Cook macaroni in boiling salted water.
Add to meat when browned the salt, pepper and paprika.
Combine meat, green pepper and onions with tomatoes. Add bacon before serving.

title: italian vegetables with pasta
directions: Chop onion coarsely; cut the remaining vegetables in one-inch chunks.
Cook all vegetables together in oil over a moderate heat until the mixture is reduced to one-half the original size. Season with salt and cook slowly for 10 minutes longer.
Mix in the grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve hot with your favorite pasta.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla, vinegar, salad oil and water.
Blend together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Frost and serve.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple thoroughly.
Add nuts, Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Let set for 24 hours.

title: potatoes italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Peel potatoes.
Dice into 1/2-inch cubes, about 8 cups.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter.
Cool and pour into plastic bag.
Add potatoes, bread crumbs and onion.
Shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Line a 14 x 10-inch baking pan with foil.
Pour potatoes in.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake uncovered until potatoes are soft, about 45 minutes.

title: 2 chocolate pies
directions: Cook all together, stirring constantly.
Pour in 2 baked pie shells.
Top with meringue.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Combine and boil sugar, corn syrup and cream to soft ball stage or until candy thermometer reaches 236°.
Work fast as you add corn flakes, peanuts and coconut.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Cut into bars and wrap in waxed paper.
Makes 16 bars.

title: jack's swedish meat balls
directions: Mix eggs, onions, 3 tablespoons cracker crumbs and salt; add 1 teaspoon allspice and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.

title: cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and milk together.
Cook for 2 minutes or until bubbly.
Add a little of the hot mixture to egg yolks. Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add margarine and vanilla.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together; add eggs.
Mix with electric mixer.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: hot pepper mustard(25 to 30 more diced, hot peppers for better mustard)
directions: In a 8-quart pot, mix diced peppers, sugar, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
In a separate bowl, mix flour and water.
Blend until smooth.
Add to the pepper mixture.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly, with wooden spoon.
Remove from heat, add pickle relish.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, molasses and butter to hard ball.
Pour over popcorn.
Butter hands and form into balls.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; drain, peel and slice lengthwise.
Arrange potatoes in a large baking dish and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of the brown sugar.
Dot with butter and orange rind.
Pour orange juice over potatoes.
Scatter remaining 2 tablespoons of brown sugar over potatoes.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Uncover and continue baking until brown and caramelized. Serves 6 to 8.

title: kahlua
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients and let cool.
Add vodka and vanilla. Put in half gallon jar and add enough water to make half-gallon. Shake for 2 days real often.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: pinto beans(lone star cafe)
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cook until done, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

If you prefer, as I do, soak overnight. You will use less than a gallon of water if you soak overnight. Cover beans well with water and cook as you always cook beans. Add seasonings after the beans are partially cooked.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix and freeze.
Cut into squares or slices.

title: german caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Combine cake mix, margarine and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread 1/2 of cake mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Drizzle caramel mixture over baked cake.
If you're going to add nuts, add to remaining cake.
Top the caramel mixture with remaining cake mixture.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°. Cool; then cut into bars.
Enjoy.

title: my mother's chocolate cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly and stir in sugar.
Add milk and butter.
Beat flour into 1/4 cup milk to smoothness and stir this and vanilla into mixture.
Cook in double boiler until quite thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from the 2 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place in a 350° oven and allow top of meringue to become a delicate brown.
(This is a very rich and creamy pie!)

title: russian tea
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use 3 teaspoonfuls (heaping) per cup of hot water.
Goes great with roaring fireplace and 3 feet of snow. Store in tightly closed container.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in hot oil for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Lower the heat; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given until batter is free of lumps.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: hot cheesy spam dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large skillet, saute spam until lightly browned; Set aside.
In a bowl, combine cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Stir in onion, horseradish, hot pepper sauce and half the Spam.
Spoon mixture into a 11 x 7- inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining Spam over cream cheese mixture.
Bake uncovered for 20 - 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with sliced green onions.
Serve with french bread for dipping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Line 9-inch plate with pastry rolled 1/4-inch thick.
Boil syrup and sugar together about two minutes.
Pour slowly over eggs, stirring well.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Turn into pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 50 minutes or until done. Pie will be done when completely puffed across top.

title: orange crush sherbet
directions: Pour ingredients in ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: chocolate-sesame sticks
directions: Combine candy coating and peanut butter in a saucepan.
Place over low heat until coating melts, stirring frequently.
Pour mixture into a 10 ounce custard cup.
Dip one end of each bread stick into coating mixture and place on wax paper until firm. Yield: 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form into a ball.
May roll in nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add lime juice and mix thoroughly.
Add thawed Cool Whip and food coloring.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with grated lime rind.
Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup coconut and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar (sprinkle brown sugar close to edge of pan because as cake rises the brown sugar moves to middle of cake).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.
Bring butter, sugar and milk to boil in small pan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining coconut.
Spoon over hot cake in pan. Serve warm or cold.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch loaf pan or three 5 3/4 x 3 1/2-inch pans.
In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda.
In another bowl, beat the eggs with the sugar, vanilla and vegetable oil until thick.
Fold dry ingredients into the beaten mixture until well-blended.
Stir in the zucchini and nuts.
Pour into prepared loaf pan or pans and bake 1 hour for large loaf or 40 to 45 minutes for small loaves, until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken.
Do not salt.
Pick chicken off the bones and put aside.
Place 1/2 the package of dressing in dish.
Pour melted margarine over it.
Place chicken on top.
Combine 2 cans of soup with 1 can of water and pour over chicken.
Place the rest of the dressing over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's jiffy rolls
directions: Pour water over yeast; add 1/2 teaspoon sugar.
Stir to dissolve and let set.
Mix milk, sugar, salt, egg and yeast with 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add melted shortening, then rest of flour or what can be stirred in well.
Cover and let rise one hour.
Turn out on floured board and shape into rolls.
Roll in melted butter and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: bean burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add beans and sauce; simmer 15 to 20 minutes on low.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: chicken, shrimp and fruit salad
directions: For Salad:
In a large bowl, combine cooked chicken or turkey, halved grapes, cubed cantaloupe or honeydew melon, water chestnuts and shrimp. Cover and chill for several hours.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook onion soup as directed on package.
Mix with mushroom soup, soy sauce and water.
In a greased roaster or casserole, place dry rice (long grain).
Pour liquid mixture in.
Add the cut up fryer on top.
Cover; cook at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes to brown.
Serves 10.

title: yummy creamed corn
directions: Let corn thaw out.
Combine corn, whipped cream, milk, salt, sugar and pepper over heat.
Mix well.
On the side melt margarine and add flour to make a paste.
Add to corn.
Cook over medium heat; don't let bottom burn.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Drain well. Melt cheese and all other ingredients. Add potatoes. Serve hot.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt and pepper.
Place ribs in broiler pan under broiler for 30 minutes.
Brown ribs and pour off grease.
Put sliced onions in crock-pot.
Slice ribs into serving pieces and put in crock-pot.
Pour on barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (high 4 to 5).

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix following ingredients and marinate 1 (4 to 5 pound) well trimmed brisket overnight or longer in refrigerator.
Place in covered plastic pan and turn several times to cover both sides well with marinade.
Bake in covered pan in 225° oven for 8 hours. Pour off liquid and cool.
Refrigerate meat until cool, slice, then put back in pan.
Cover with barbecue sauce.
Serve heated.

title: molded shrimp dip
directions: Melt the cheese into soup over low heat, stirring well. Remove and stir in the celery, onions and horseradish.
Mix the gelatin into a little cold water and stir into the tomato mixture. Mix in the sour cream and mayonnaise.
Fold in the shrimp.
Pour into a mold sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Chill for a few hours; serve with crackers.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips in microwave on medium for 6-7 minutes. Stir a couple of times until smooth. When melted add salted peanuts and stir well. Drop by tsp. onto waxed paper.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cover cabbage with water and cook 10 minutes; drain.
Make a white sauce from the butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Stir constantly until thickened.

title: pizza pie
directions: Mix beef with salt and pepper; pat out in a 9-inch pie plate. Spread tomatoes over meat and sprinkle with remaining ingredients. Bake at 375° for a good 20 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring the oil, vinegar and sugar to a boil and cool.
Pour over the vegetables. Place it back into the large jar the sauerkraut came in and cover. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: "greek style" stewed green beans
directions: In a large saucepan, heat oil; saute onion until transparent. Add garlic and cook 1 minute longer.
Add tomatoes, parsley, mint and oregano and bring to boil.
Snip off ends and any strings from beans.
Add beans to sauce mixture.
Lower heat; cover and simmer until tender, about 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Can be eaten hot or at room temperature.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine cooked chicken, Italian dressing and dry taco mix. Bring to boil. Spoon into tortillas and roll up. Cover with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Mix together
soup,
dressing and preserves.
Pour over chicken until completely
covered.
Put
in large pan and bake until done at 350° for 1
hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine in large Dutch oven until tender.
Add next nine ingredients; cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat and mash vegetables with a potato masher (slightly).
Add milk, sour cream, soup and cheese, stirring constantly until all is blended. Garnish bowls of soup with bacon strips.

title: cherry topped cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Press into bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Chill one hour.
Beat cream cheese with sugar until creamy.
Blend in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Spread pie filling around edge.
Chill at least three hours before serving.

title: indoor barbecue
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken in milk, then in dry ingredients.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes enough for 2 fryers.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add ketchup, barbecue sauce and mustard. Mix instant coffee in water, then add, along with brown sugar. Let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Spoon over rolls or hamburger buns.
Serves 4.

title: easy 5 fruit salad
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: oatmeal-spice cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves on a sheet of waxed paper.
Shape dough in two 8-inch long rolls.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and chill until firm, about 4 hours in refrigerator, 3 hours in freezer.
(If freezing longer than 3 hours, let stand at room temperature for 20 minutes before slicing.)

title: jam
directions: Cut up rhubarb and add sugar.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Put in large pan and bring to a boil and cook 12 minutes.
Add 1 box jello and mix until dissolved.
Put in hot jars.
Seal, then use hot water bath process for 10 minutes.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Thoroughly cream butter and sugar. Add egg, milk, vanilla and almond extract; beat well. Stir together flour and baking powder; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing to make a smooth dough. Do not chill. Place dough in a cookie press and press cookies onto ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate, if desired. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Remove cookies from sheet and cool on rack.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Combine Miracle Whip, cheese, milk and salt.
Cook rotini according to package directions.
Combine cooked noodles, chicken, tomatoes, peppers and onion.
Add dressing to salad mixture and stir well.
Chill.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place ingredients in layers in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2 of the juice from the beans over the casserole.
Top with Tater Tots.
Pour soup over Tater Tots. Bake
at 375° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix gelatine and water. Add scalded milk. Mix well. Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add cream and milk. Freeze. Makes 6 quarts.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Cool, debone and cut up.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix in cracker crumbs.
Spread buttered cracker crumbs on top and bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: 5 year pickles
directions: Use stone jar, plastic tub or something like that.
Put in layer of cucumbers, layer of sugar and so on until all is used. Add spices.
Using your hand, mix from the top to bottom until sugar is dissolved.
This will make the syrup.
Store in same container or put in glass jars.
Will keep for a long time.

title: meatball soup(serves 6)
directions: Make meatballs.
