In medium bowl combine beef, egg, 3 tablespoons water, bread crumbs, salt and parsley.
Mix lightly and shape into 24 balls.
In hot butter in a 4 1/2-quart kettle saute meatballs, a single layer at a time until browned on all sides. Drain off fat.
Set meatballs aside.

title: pineapple supreme salad
directions: Mix dry pudding into Cool Whip and then add rest of ingredients and mix well and refrigerate.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix water and yeast; set aside.
Mix sugar and melted butter. Add egg alternately.
Add flour and yeast mixture to egg mixture. Put in airtight bowl in refrigerator.
Dough is better cold or made the night before.
Grease muffin tins, stir dough and spoon in muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 36 rolls.
Dough will keep a week
or more.

title: vegetable chilli
directions: Heat oil.
Add onion and saute for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Cover and cook or simmer for 10 minutes.
Add beans, pepper, corn and zucchini.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain beans slightly.
Mix with sugar and pepper.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pieces of bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sara's  crabmeat-stuffed mushrooms(low salt)
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; mince stems.
Saute stems in 2 tablespoons butter until brown.
Drain crabmeat and remove filament.
In a bowl, add crabmeat to mushroom stems.
Add bread crumbs, garlic, oregano, cheese, potassium (or salt) and pepper. Mix well; set aside.
Heat remaining butter in skillet; add mushroom caps and stir gently until tender.
Drain well. Stuff mushroom caps with crabmeat mixture.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes until bubbly.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar with oil and applesauce. Stir soda into hot water, then add cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and eggs. After blending add raisins, walnuts and flour. Pour into well greased and floured cake mold and bake at 350° until done (approximately 1 hour 20 minutes).

title: chicken a la orange
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, combine butter, sugar and orange juice.
Cook over high heat, stirring occasionally until thickened (12 to 17 minutes).
Arrange chicken in 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, until tender, brushing with sauce every 15 minutes.
Cut orange colored peel from orange.
Cut half of the peel into narrow strips and add to remaining sauce.
Slice orange into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip slices in sauce and arrange on serving platter with chicken.
Serve with additional warm sauce. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 14-inch cookie sheet with crescent roll dough, patting and stretching to fit pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 or 8 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool.

title: chili
directions: Cook onions and garlic in tabs of grease until done.
Add meat; cook until done.
Pour chili powder in meat and mix well. Add boiling water.
Add other ingredients.
Salt to taste.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add 1 or more drops of hot sauce.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix egg yolks, light cream and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until slightly thickened.
Let cool. When cool, add fruit and marshmallows; refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan; cook over medium heat.
Add butter, lemon juice, rind, egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Fold sour cream into cooled mixture.
Spoon into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Spread whipped cream over pie and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler.
Mix sugar, flour, egg yolks and salt together and small amount of scalded milk.
Mix well and add this mixture to remaining scalded milk.
Stir well. Cool in top of double boiler until thickened. Add vanilla, butter and coconut. Pour in baked pie shell. Top with meringue; brown.

title: bread custard
directions: Place broken rolls in bottom of baking dish, 6 x 9-inches. Add raisins.
Mix other ingredients and pour over rolls.
Bake at 325°
for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pecan teasers
directions: Bread slices may be cut into shapes with a cookie cutter - stars are nice at Christmas.
Cook bacon until very crisp and drain.
Blend other ingredients with bacon.
Spread bread lightly with butter,
then spread mixture.	Bake at 350° until lightly brown about 5-7 minutes.

title: bordelaise sauce
directions: Place the wine and soup stock together in a small saucepan and reduce the liquid to half.
Saute mushrooms and shallots in butter until tender; add to the wine mixture.
Add parsley, salt and pepper and simmer for a few minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch and water mixture.
Delicious on meats of any kind.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. You may add garlic.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage into medium pieces.
Spread in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Brown meat and onion in a large skillet, breaking up meat with a large spoon as it cooks.
Stir in rice, salt and pepper. Spoon mixture over cabbage.
In a small saucepan, heat tomato soup and water to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover casserole tightly with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and fluff lightly with fork before serving.

title: caramel graham squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch pan with graham crackers.
Sprinkle "evenly" with marshmallows.
In a small saucepan, combine margarine and brown sugar and cook over medium heat.
Bring to a boil, then let boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture evenly over the marshmallows.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pick chicken.
Cut into bite-size pieces and arrange in casserole.
Mix together soup, milk and stock.
Pour over chicken. Top with chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix stuffing with melted butter and top casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes covered at 350°.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.
Can be made the day before but leave off stuffing until ready to cook.

title: fresh fruit delight
directions: Cut angel food cake to cover bottom of oblong baking dish. Add 1 package of strawberries and 1 package of blueberries, then add the Cool Whip.
Garnish top with remaining strawberries and blueberries.
Place in refrigerator and serve cold.

title: sweet mustard dressing
directions: Mix well. Chill. Serve with salad, ham and beef.

title: evelyn's flank steak
directions: Score top of steak.
Rub with garlic powder and Tabasco.
Pour Kikkoman soy sauce over steak.
Marinate at least 6 hours.
Cook on grill, about 8 minutes on one side and 7 minutes on other side. Makes great sandwiches on sesame seed buns with Dijon mustard.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Steam broccoli and drain well.
Mix soups, ham and milk; simmer.
Add broccoli; cook for 30 minutes or until good and hot. Good served with corn muffins.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Split and layer strawberries on bottom of crust (just enough to cover bottom).
Chop rest of strawberries and add sugar and jello with just enough water to dissolve jello.
Boil and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate and top with Cool Whip.

title: yams with orange sauce
directions: Boil yams first.
Remove skins and cut yams into 1 1/2-inch pieces, then place in greased casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over yams.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: gerry's chocolate mocha mousse
directions: Brush both sides of eggplant slices with the oil; sprinkle lightly with salt.
In large skillet, brown eggplant slices, about 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Drain and set aside.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
When dough is thoroughly chilled, roll into balls and press out on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: beet gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Pour off beet juice and save 1 cup. Combine with water to make 1 cup if necessary.
Combine with gelatin.
Put layers of beets in bottom of mold.
Cover with some liquid.
Let set.
Make another layer of beets, etc.
Layer so beets don't float.
Set.
Serve with mayonnaise and crumbly Blue cheese, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Pare and cut up apples and arrange in pie shell. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples. Mix 1/3 cup sugar with flour and cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done. If pie browns too quickly, cover edges with foil.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook noodles, uncovered, in boiling water for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally; drain.
Combine the soup, milk, water and Cheddar cheese in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until the cheese melts and sauce is hot.
Stir in cooked noodles, turkey, peas and carrots.
Spoon the mixture into greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix cake mix, eggs and margarine and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: aunt sue's yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
lukewarm water; let set 5 minutes. Add milk,
Crisco
and	sugar.	Add
mixture to flour.	Knead well. Put
in
refrigerator and leave 1 day.
Roll out rolls, cut and let set 3 hours before baking at 375°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix altogether and refrigerate overnight.
Mix in tall can of sliced water chestnuts.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
This can be frozen.

title: gazpacho salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine corn oil, vinegar, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well. Cover and chill.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: emily's molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, molasses and egg with oil or shortening; set aside. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and spice mix.
Add molasses mixture to flour mixture; blend and chill about 1 hour. Roll into balls 1 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork tines.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese squares
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: pizza burger
directions: Cut French bread in half lengthwise. Brown ground beef in skillet. Add tomato soup, onion, Parmesan cheese, ketchup, bell pepper, oregano, salt and garlic salt. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Spread meat mixture on cut sides of bread. Sprinkle with cheese. Broil until cheese is bubbly. Cut into diagonal slices.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the filling ingredients together. Divide and spread over tortillas, roll up.

title: italian stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Remove stems and chop fine.
Remove sausage from casing and saute in pan with stems, garlic and 1 tablespoon oil.
Add cheese and parsley.
Fill mushroom caps, rounding tops, and put in a shallow baking pan.
Add water and 1 tablespoon oil to pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a soft ball.
Pour half of mixture into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cook other mixture until it forms a cracking ball.
Pour into egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add nuts; drop teaspoonful on tinfoil.

title: dustin's chocolate squares
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and butter.
Mix thoroughly. Spread evenly in a 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peking roast
directions: Cut 1-inch slits into sides of the meat all around.
Press small wedges of onion and garlic alternately into each slit (garlic may be omitted).
Place in a large bowl or plastic bag. Pour 1 cup vinegar over meat.
Refrigerate for 24 to 48 hours, turning occasionally.

title: strata breakfast casserole
directions: Prepare asparagus, cut in 1 inch pieces, steam, covered with 1 Tbsp oil, salt and 1/3 c. water for 3-4 minutes.
Whisk half and half, eggs, salt and pepper.
Spray a 9x13 pyrex baking dish with Pam.
Line bottom with 6 slices of bread.
Scatter half of the meat and asparagus over the bread, sprinkle with half of the scallions and cheese.
Pour 1 c. of egg mixture over the top. Repeat layers with remaining bread, meat and asparagus, cheese and scallions.
Slowly pour remaining egg mixture over top.
Cover with plastic wrap, then weight down casserole with 3
16 oz. can for 15 minutes to submerge ingredients.
Can be refrigerated overnight, but return to room temperature before baking.
Put oven rack to middle position, bake at 325 about 50 minutes, turn on broiler and broil until strata is spotty brown and puffy (watch carefully).
Let stand for 8 minutes; serve immediately.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Mix powdered sugar and cocoa in mixing bowl; cream together with butter.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Add peanut butter and knead by hand.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch well buttered cake pan. Let stand a few minutes and cut into squares.
Yield: 35 to 40 pieces.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn in milk; stir in beaten egg, cracker crumbs, green pepper, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: chicken ala glekas
directions: Rinse and clean chicken; dry with paper towels.
Mix salt, pepper and oregano together.
Rub seasoning mix on both sides of chicken.
Place chicken in a roasting pan with the skin up. Sprinkle mix of oil and lemon juice on top of chicken.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn chicken on other side and add 1/4 cup water; continue baking at 400° for another 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients on High in microwave (4 1/2 minutes). Pour popcorn into large paper bag.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn in bag.
Fold top of bag down and shake.
Microwave on High for one minute and 20 seconds.
Shake well and cook again on High one minute and 20 seconds.
Shake well and cook 30 seconds longer.
Pour in bowl and cool.
Break pieces apart before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed and let cool. Mix pudding when cake is ready to be layered. Cut or crumble cake and start layering ingredients in a large punch bowl.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Melt butter in baking dish in 350° oven.
Pound chicken breasts to flatten as evenly as possible.
Top each with 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese.
Roll up tightly, beginning with narrow end.
Secure with toothpicks.
Coat rolled breasts in melted butter, then roll in crumbs.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove toothpicks to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: yankee baked beans
directions: Place beans in a 4-quart cooking pot; cover with cold water and let soak overnight.
In the morning pour out the water, then cover beans with fresh water.
Add the salt pork and the onion which has been cut into fine pieces.
Bring to a boil and simmer at least 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Place beans and onion into a baking pan with enough juice to nearly cover the beans.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with catsup or chili sauce.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Combine flour, egg, milk and salt. Make a very stiff dough. May be necessary to add more flour to get the right consistency. Roll out and slice.
Remove chicken from bones; cut into small pieces.
Drop noodles into boiling broth; simmer 30 minutes or more.
Do not boil noodles.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion; then mix with soups, tomatoes, melted oleo, washed rice, salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and then bake covered for approximately 1 hour until rice is well done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Over low heat, mix butter, cream, chicken broth and cheese, stirring often.
Mix until all ingredients come together into a sauce.
In a casserole dish, put chicken and broccoli along the bottom.
Pour sauce over it, then add the rice to the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well. Add syrup and mix.
Sift flour, salt and ginger and fold in cream mixture.
Dissolve soda in boiling water.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When partly cool, cut in squares.

title: heavenly hamburger
directions: Brown the chuck and onion, then add the remaining ingredients. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop up cabbage.
Cut up onions (green tops and bottoms). Dice tomatoes and chop bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise; salt and pepper to taste.

title: new england maple ribs
directions: Combine all ingredients except ribs; pour over ribs. Refrigerate at least 4 hours, turning occasionally.
Grill or broil ribs as desired, basting frequently with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
A small amount of grated carrot or red pepper may be added for color.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Use a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Grease with cooking spray.
Mix baking powder, salt, flour and sugar.
Reserve 1 tablespoon margarine for crumb topping.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients until smooth.
Fold in drained shrimp.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onions in bacon drippings until tender.
Add chicken broth, potatoes, creamed corn, bacon, milk and seasonings.
Heat. Do not boil.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Break lettuce in bite-size pieces.
Cook bacon.
Drain and crumble.
Layer lettuce, celery, eggs, peas, peppers, onion and bacon in order given.
Combine sugar and mayonnaise.
Spread over top of salad.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.
Serves 12.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix well; form into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet; freeze.
After frozen, place in plastic bags in freezer until needed.
Bake frozen in preheated oven at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: banana-pecan bread
directions: Beat the sugars and oil until blended. Add the eggs and beat until smooth. Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the sugar mixture, beating. Fold in the bananas and pecans. Pour the batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven until set, about 1 hour. Cool briefly in the pan, then transfer to a rack to cool completely. Makes one 9-inch loaf.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichokes in quarters.
Add all ingredients and mix together.
Put in lightly greased (use oil) Pyrex pie plate 9-inch or low quiche dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use any kind of crackers.
This is delicious!
Double recipe for more people.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, add minced onions, Worcestershire sauce and ham or dried beef.
Form into ball; roll in chopped walnuts, place on plate.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend all the ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: first down dip(microwave)
directions: Microwave process cheese spread and sour cream in small bowl on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Serve warm with soft pretzels, chips and vegetable dippers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups. Preparation time:
10 minutes; cooking time:
3 minutes.

title: buffet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and 1/2 cup melted butter in large bowl. Stir in sour cream, soup, onion, cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine cornflake crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix cabbage, onions, noodles and chicken breast.
Toast sesame seed and slivered almonds in butter until lightly brown.

title: crazy cake
directions: Pour 1 cup cold water over all and mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9-inch square pan.

title: mr. bill's pearly gate cake
directions: Blend shortenin' 'n sugah wid mixer.
Sift flour, bakin' powder 'n salt 3 times.
Now alternately add flour mixture 'n watar (2 tablespoons at a time) to the sugah mixture.
Add 1/2 uv aig whites.
Keep on puttin' in flour 'n water til al gone.
Now add remaining aig whites 'n extracts.
Mix 'n pore in 3 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 325° fur 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 'n frost wid favorite icin.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash and cut up chicken.
Rub chicken with salt, pepper and Accent.
Place flour in a bag and place chicken, a few pieces at a time, in bag.
Shake to coat chicken.
Put oil in pan and allow it to get hot, then add floured chicken.
Cook until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Combine broccoli, oranges, onions, raisins and bacon.
Add dressing, toss to coat and refrigerate at least one hour before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, tomato, olives, cheese and kidney beans. Add drained ground beef and chili powder.
Stir in Fritos and Catalina.

title: meatballs lasagna style
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion and green pepper.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs in greased dish.
Spoon cottage cheese and sauce around meatballs, covering them all over.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: chocolate rolls
directions: Roll your dough a lot.
Roll out a piece of biscuit dough the size of a plate; roll thin.
Spread cocoa all over the dough, then add your sugar and then your butter covering completely.
Turn down each end of the dough, then turn each side in to meet.
Pack it hard and then put it in a pan.
Sprinkle some sugar on top and pinch a little butter on it.
Pack it down good in the pan before you sprinkle the sugar on it.

title: swiss steak and rice
directions: Pour oil in Dutch oven.
Add steak and brown on both sides. Turn down on low heat.
Cover.
Cook for 1 hour until tender. Check during cooking and keep water enough to cover meat while cooking.
Use your favorite steak sauce, ketchup or barbecue sauce to make a thin gravy.
Cook rice to serve steak over.

title: spritz
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar gradually; continue mixing until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg. Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually add to butter mixture; blend well.
Add almond extract, if desired.
Food coloring may be added if colored dough is desired.
Force through cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers, onions and pepper in thin slices.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Cool.
Store in freezer containers and freeze.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix everything but milk.
Add milk to desired consistency. Make into balls or drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.

title: superb chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet.
Add kidney beans, tomato soup, water and chili powder to taste.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch together for 2 minutes or until thick.
Take off stove and add Jell-O.
Pour in crust (baked) over fresh strawberries.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: lemon butter frosting
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add liquid and salt.
Makes 3 1/2 cups of frosting.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, parsley, basil and garlic; mix well. Add cheese, broccoli and noodles; mix lightly.
Chill.
Arrange tomatoes on platter.
Top salad with chopped walnuts.

title: beef burritos
directions: Brown meat. Add onions, flour, tomatoes and small amount of water. Let cook until water is gone. Warm tortillas and fill with meat mixture.

title: mussels baresse
directions: After cleaning mussels, place in baking dish and add garlic and sprinkle with parsley, black pepper, salt, oregano, bread crumbs and paprika.
Cover bottom of baking dish with chicken broth and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: trash
directions: You will need 1 large trash bag.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Work the sugar, flour, and butter together until like meal.

title: herb tomato tart
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in skillet. Add onions and saute until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.

Stir in flour; set aside. Beat eggs and milk. Add salt, pepper and herbs. Place onions and cheese into pie crust. Cover with egg mixture. Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°. Bake 15 minutes. Arrange tomato slices on top and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: orange bran cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Form into 2 rolls (1 1/2-inches in diameter); wrap in aluminum foil.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Slice thin.
Place on greased baking sheets. Bake at 400° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: cocoa drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour, soda, cocoa and salt.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and cheese in double boiler.
Cook broccoli by package directions.
Combine.
Cover with Ritz crackers and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: honey carrots
directions: Wash and tip carrots.
Cook in a small amount of boiling salted water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.

title: english muffins
directions: Knead just until easy to handle.

title: krista's one dish meal
directions: Boil noodles in water until tender. While noodles boil, saute ground beef; drain. Rinse noodles in cold water. Put back in pot with 1/2 cup of water. Add ground beef and remaining ingredients. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix water and beef broth with all the spices. Bake with meat at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Keep basting.
Or place meat and spices, water and broth in crock-pot and cook on low 7 to 8 hours.

title: happiness cake
directions: Add wet to dry ingredients (except poppy seed).
Beat 4 minutes with mixer.
Fold in poppy seed.
Pour in a Bundt or angel food pan (greased).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 1/2 hour. Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat, add sliced smoked sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic; saute until tender.
Add beans and next 7 ingredients (stewed tomatoes to bay leaf).
Cover, reduce heat to simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve over rice with additional hot sauce.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with assorted chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Mix 4 pounds sugar and water.
Bring to a full rolling boil. Drop apples in water while boiling and stir.
Mix cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, 1 cup sugar, allspice and salt.
Mix with apples and boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir all together.

title: seven-can seafood casserole(microwave oven)
directions: Combine all ingredients except onion rings; blend well.
Place in 3-quart glass casserole; cover.
Microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until heated through.
Top with onion rings.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: macaroni chicken surprise
directions: In large bowl, mix together, cooked and drained macaroni and chicken.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In small bowl, stir warm chicken broth into sour cream until smooth.
Add egg and mustard, mixing well.
Pour over ingredients in large bowl.
Add pimento and 1 1/4 cups of the shredded cheese.
Mix well and pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peach preserves
directions: Combine peaches and sugar in a heavy pot and let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Boil gently until fruit becomes clear and syrup is thick.
Stir often to prevent sticking.
A dash of lemon juice will help taste and prevent sugar crystals forming.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Put sauerkraut in colander to drain, then add celery, green pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil. Pour over the kraut mixture.
Let stand overnight.

title: turtle cake
directions: Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake cake according to directions. While cake is still hot, prick holes and pour condensed milk over top. Cool. Pour caramel topping over and cover with whipped cream and nuts.

title: company lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, salt, pepper, parsley flakes, onion and oregano.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and a little water. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Mix together all cheese, except Parmesan. Boil together 2 quarts of water and 1 tablespoon oil
dropped into water.
Drop in lasagna noodles.
Boil for 15 minutes. Drain.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix gelatin and water.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese with sugar.
Add this to gelatin mixture.
In another bowl, beat milk until it peaks, then add to the other mixture.
Add blueberries and vanilla.
Pour in pan and let set.

title: gooseberry jelly(tart)
directions: In a large kettle, pour juice; heat.
I add pectin as juice becomes warm.
Bring to rolling boil.
Add sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar completely.
Continue to stir once in a while. Boil at least 3 minutes or boil until a rolling boil cannot be stirred away.
Remove from heat.
Skim off scum.
Seal in sterile jars or seal with paraffin.

title: unbelievable lasagne
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, spread 1 cup sauce and 1 layer uncooked lasagne.
Top with some sauce, Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan. Repeat.
End with sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until light brown and bubbling.
Allow to stand for 15 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: elf's cookies
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make layers using the first seven ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool and cut into blocks.

title: breakfast pizza supreme
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Separate rolls into 16
triangles.
Press over bottom and sides of 12-inch pizza pan.

title: marie's banana salad
directions: Slice bananas crossways and put over lettuce.
Dilute mayonnaise with milk; add sugar and pour over lettuce.
Sprinkle chopped peanuts on top if you like.

title: clams casino
directions: Place rock salt 1/2-inch deep in a shallow baking pan.
Scrub clams thoroughly.
Open and discard 1/2 the shell.
Cut clam into quarters and place in the bottom of the shell. Settle clam shells in the bed of rock salt. This will prevent them from spilling their juices.
Melt butter in frying pan and saute onion, garlic and pepper until onion is transparent.
Remove from heat and add salt, black and cayenne peppers, bread crumbs, parsley and lemon juice.
Mix together and spoon onto the clams. Top with a piece of bacon. Bake in a 500° oven for 5 minutes or until hot.
Serve hot with lemon wedges on a bed of hot rock salt.

title: spinach salad
directions: Amounts of ingredients can vary according to your preference.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Peel potatoes when cool and grate. Add sour cream, cottage cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Put into buttered dish.
Top with cheese; cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: toffee topped bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan. In large mixing bowl, mix together brown sugar and flour using pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and set aside.
To mixture in large bowl, add baking powder and salt, then using a fork, lightly beat in vanilla, milk and egg.
Beat until mixture is smooth. Pour batter into prepared pan.
In small bowl, combine chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Sprinkle reserved mixture over batter in pan, then sprinkle chocolate chip mixture.
Spread evenly and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool bars completely before cutting.
Store in airtight container. Makes 24 brownies.

title: egg harbor tomato(low-fat)
directions: Cook potato, onion, celery and garlic in water until tender. Stir in tomato juice, milk, soup, parsley, garlic, thyme and pepper.
Heat through and serve the next day.

title: coconut candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until soft ball when dropped in water. Add coconut and boil 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add vinegar.
Beat until smooth and creamy. Add vanilla. Drop on waxed paper.

title: million dollar cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Add egg.
Add flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Dough is easier to handle if chilled.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Press with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook cornbread according to package directions. Toast loaf of bread and tear into small pieces. Saute chopped celery and onions. Mix eggs, chicken broth, cornbread, bread pieces, celery and onions together. Add salt, pepper and sage to taste. Add turkey broth (or additional chicken broth) until consistency of thick bread batter. Pour into 15 x 11 x 2-inch baking dish. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: sole vanessi
directions: Place fish on waxed paper and sprinkle lightly with salt and white pepper.
On each sole fillet, place 1/2 cheese slice, 1 ounce crab meat, a sprinkle of basil and 1 sliced mushroom.
Roll up and place seam side down in a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Set aside.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook vegetables in oleo until tender.
Blend in flour and salt.
Combine soup and milk; add to vegetable mixture and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp pieces and pour into 1-quart casserole dish.
Combine the tablespoon oleo and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Place hash browns in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add onion on top.
Pour 1/2 of the melted butter on the top.
Mix together soup, Cheez Whiz and sour cream.
Pour on top.
Cover with corn flake crumbs and rest of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine the three ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Peel cucumbers, if desired, and slice thinly.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients and stir well.
Stir cucumbers into sour cream mixture.
Cover and chill.
Serves 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Whip all ingredients together and spread in shallow baking dish.

title: chocolate sheet cake(makes one 15 x 10-inch cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small saucepan melt 1 cup margarine.
Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa and then water.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place "toast points" in 10 x 10-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
In a separate container combine soup, 1/2 cup of juice, salt and pepper.
Place asparagus on toast, pour mixture over asparagus, sprinkle with grated egg and top with grated cheese. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: molasses banana bread(low-fat)
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in egg, bananas and molasses.
Mix in remaining ingredients just until blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes. Cool on wire rack.

title: barb's big cookies
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine over low heat.
Add to sugars, eggs and peanut butter, beating until smooth.
Add all of the remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop on cookie sheet with an ice cream scoop.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together whole
corn,
creamed corn and sour cream. Place corn mixture in casserole and heat in oven while preparing corn muffin mix.
Pour muffin mix over corn mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: jelly filled muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl. Make a well in the center of dry ingredients. Pour in liquid ingredients in the well and mix until just moistened. Fill in greased muffin pans 1/3 to 3/4 full of batter. Spoon 1 teaspoon of jelly or jam on top. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Very light and tasty. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach and remove stems; dry leaves.
Tear greens into bite size pieces.
Heat salad dressing in chafing dish.
Add remaining ingredients and toss until greens are well coated. Makes 6 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, carrot, lemon juice, egg, flour, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet.
Spoon 5 pancakes, 1 heaping tablespoonful each, into oil; cook 1 1/2 minutes per side.
Transfer to towel to drain.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Serve with applesauce or sour cream if desired.

title: jimmy dean country breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan well.
Place bread in pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine rest of ingredients together and mix well. Pour over bread; refrigerate overnight.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apricot cookies
directions: Chop apricots.
Cover with boiling water for 5 minutes; drain. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet; bake about 12 minutes at 325°.

title: thanksgiving squash
directions: Cook squash and drain well.
Slice onion, grate carrot, add butter and cook in microwave oven for 3 minutes.
Mix cooked onion and carrot, sour cream, mushroom soup, salt, pepper, squash and 3/4 stuffing mix.
Pour into casserole.
Mix remainder of stuffing with melted butter and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Put in the refrigerator for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine cooked macaroni, cheese, soup, mushrooms, milk, onion and 1 cup crushed cheese crackers.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup crushed cheese crackers on top of mixture.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar; beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add melted chocolate, instant coffee and rum extract.
Stir in flour and broken walnuts and turn into pie shell.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup walnut halves. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes. Cool. Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: pork or beef tenderloin, chicken, pork or beef roasts, any fish,
directions: Preheat outdoor grill on medium.
Place steak or fillet on foil large enough to wrap or enclose steak or fillet.
Mix ingredients and pour or spread evenly over steak/fillet.
Turn grill to low and place wrapped and sealed in foil steak/fillet on grill.
Heat for 15 to 20 minutes depending on grill.
Enjoy!
Great with asparagus and baked potato.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix rest of ingredients together and mix with spaghetti.
Let stand overnight.

title: pecan treats
directions: Melt margarine and pour over brown sugar.
Add eggs and other ingredients; mix well.
Flour a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into small squares.

title: chicken stew
directions: Cook chicken until done in large pot.
Use only enough water to cook.
In a large iron pot on high, cook salted pork until done. Remove pork meat and about half of grease.
Turn down to medium-high heat.
Add onions; cook about 5 minutes, then add tomato juice, sauce, chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Yield:
About 1 gallon.

title: sweetened condensed milk(mock)
directions: Combine in blender.
Makes equivalent to 14 ounce can sweetened condensed milk.
Store in refrigerator.

title: apple slice
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Put egg yolk in measuring cup and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to shortening. Mix.
Shape into ball.
Roll 1/2 of the dough into 15 x 11. Transfer to cookie sheet.
Cover with apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out rest of dough and place over apples. Pinch edges together.
Beat egg white and spread on top of crust. Bake in 400° oven 20 to 30 minutes.
While dough is hot, drizzle glaze over top.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Mix cream cheese, ham, chives in large bowl.
Clean chicken beasts and pound flat.
Take spoonful of mixture and place it in the center of a chicken breast.
Roll breast and wrap it with a slice of bacon.
Place in nonstick baking dish.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake for additional 15 to 20 minutes until chicken is brown, bacon cooked.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into a large bowl. Sprinkle pudding mix over pineapple and mix well.
Add rest of fruit and chill.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Slice the hot dogs, mash the potatoes and shred the cheese. Mix all together like a casserole.
Spread catsup evenly over all. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: yogurt muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients with a fork until well mixed.
Stir together liquid ingredients slightly.
Blend with dry mixture only until combined.
Avoid overmixing.
Spoon into greased muffin tins or use paper baking cups.
Bake 15 minutes. Leftovers freeze well.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Saute hamburger, bacon and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer about 15 minutes in large skillet.
If I don't have all the varieties of beans, I substitute 2 of 1 kind, etc.

title: reuben loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix in enough of the 1 cup flour to make soft dough.
Knead 4 minutes. Roll on greased baking sheet to 14 x 10-inches.
Spread center with dressing and top with corned beef, sauerkraut and cheese. Cut 1-inch strip along sides and fold over the center by alternating the sides.
Cover and place sheet pan over a pan half filled with boiling water, about 15 minutes.
Brush with egg white and top with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Take off bone and cut into small pieces.
Save broth.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Line baking dish with 1/3 of stuffing mix.
Add layer of chicken, then pour can of mushroom soup mixed with can of broth over chicken.
Add another layer of stuffing mix, layer of chicken, then pour can of chicken soup mixed with can of broth over this.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate coronet
directions: Sprinkle ladyfingers with sherry.
Arrange ladyfingers around a large (9 or 10-inch) spring-form pan.
Put remaining ladyfingers on bottom of pan.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Beat until well blended and smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat until smooth.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in with whipped heavy cream.
Add chocolate into cream cheese mixture. Pour into pan and chill until firm.
No baking necessary.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Chop up broccoli, cauliflower and onion; mix sugar and vinegar in.
Add pepper, salt, sour cream and Miracle Whip in large bowl.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cream the cream cheese and rest of ingredients; mix well.
Add crab and place in ovenproof dish; cover with sliced almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Place in bottom of pie shell.
Sprinkle some chopped onion over sausage.
Top with thick layer of grated cheese.
Mix together the eggs, milk and 1 teaspoon salt.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 45 minutes).

title: cherry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth and gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping and spoon in crust.
Chill for 4 hours.
Spoon cherry pie filling over top of pie and serve.

title: italian chicken and tomatoes
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasonings on one side.
Place slice of cheese on top of chicken.
Flour the chicken and roll up.
Brown in a little oil.
Pour tomatoes over top and let simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Spread mixture into bottom of baked pie shell.
Fill with strawberries; gently press into cheese.
Over low heat, melt jelly.
Stir until smooth, cool and spoon over berries.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: mexican "taco" dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and water. Cook until dry.
On a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet spread refried beans.
Cover with ground beef mixture.
Spread with sour cream and taco sauce.
Sprinkle onions over the top, then cover with grated cheese.
Garnish with tomatoes and olives.
Serve with taco chips.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in a bowl and mix well with mixer.
Pour into ice cream freezer and add condensed milk. Stir well and fill to line on freezer with whole milk.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Put 1/2 of ham, potatoes and onion in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1/2 of shredded cheese.
Repeat layers. Spread undiluted soup evenly over top so air doesn't reach potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours, or until tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Pull meat off bones and put in pieces in baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and put on top of chicken.
Melt butter with crushed cracker crumbs and put on top of chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach jumbo shells
directions: Simmer spinach for 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain well and chop.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Add spinach and heat.
Combine egg, cheeses, nutmeg and spinach.
Stuff 20 cooked shells; cover with sauce.

title: white yeast bread
directions: Add yeast to water; set aside to soften.
Heat milk in large pan until bubbles form at the edges.
Add salt, milk and oil, then cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups flour; stir to make a smooth batter.
Add egg and yeast; blend well.
Add remaining flour to form dough.
Knead dough on floured board until smooth.
Let it rise in greased, covered pan until double in bulk.
Fold dough down.
Let it rest 5 minutes.
Shape into rolls or loaves in greased pans.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes for rolls or 25 to 30 minutes for loaves.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Note:
Half the shortening can be replaced with butter or margarine.

title: pizza burger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Add Italian seasoning. Add pizza sauce, tomato paste and soup.
Boil macaroni until tender. Add to preceding.
Mix and pour into large casserole dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kiwi fruit salad and honey yogurt dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well until blended.
Dressing per tablespoon has 53 calories, 39 grams of protein, 2 grams of carbohydrates, 5 grams total fat, 4 milligrams of cholesterol and 39 milligrams of sodium.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: cherry jello salad
directions: Boil 1 can Dr. Pepper to mix the Jello with, then add 1 cold can of Dr. Pepper and pecans. Chill.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine rice and cheese.
Combine eggs, parsley and salt.
Add the mixtures, and stir into the spinach.
Pour into an oiled 1-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs mixed with oil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: guilt-free pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until combined.
Gradually add egg substitute, beating well; set aside.
Combine sour cream and baking soda; set aside.
Combine flour and salt and, at low speed, add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes or until wood pick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Yield: 24 servings.
Per serving:
Calories 250, Fat 7.7 g, Cholesterol 6 mg, Sodium 152 mg.

title: pecan pie filling
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Add corn syrup, margarine, vanilla, salt, and flour.
Beat on high for 2 min.
Add pecans. Pour into two of your favorite 9 in. unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300°F for 30-40 min.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and peanut butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls.
Put in a casserole dish.
You can brown the meat balls before you bake them if you want.
Cover them with tomato juice and sliced green pepper. Cover with aluminum and bake on 350° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Melt butter, pour over sugar, add flour, 3 eggs and other ingredients.
Mix and add last 3 eggs; pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and test with a toothpick.
If comes out clean remove and let cool for 10 minutes. If not done, check again in about 10 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: With a wire whisk, stir together undiluted juice and mixture of cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Heat to consistency of gravy. Pour over apples.
Turn
mixture into prepared pie shell; dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust; cut slits in crust to allow steam to escape.
Sprinkle lightly with water and nutmeg to taste. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 more minutes.

title: sausage and wild rice
directions: Cook rice as directed. Mix soup, milk and mushrooms. Add browned sausage and cooked rice. Pour into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: spicy broccoli-orzo salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and toss.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or for at least 3 hours for flavors to blend.
Serve chilled or room temperature.
Serves 4.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine popcorn and pecans in a lightly greased large roasting pan; set aside.
Combine peanuts and the next 3 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour peanut mixture over popcorn mixture; stir with a lightly greased long handled spoon until popcorn mixture is coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter oat bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine margarine, peanut butter, brown sugar, corn syrup, and vanilla; gradually add oats.
Press into a greased 9 X 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 12-14 minutes. Cool on wire rack 5 minutes.

title: scalloped corn
directions: In a large frypan cook onion in margarine until golden. Remove from
heat.
Quickly
stir
in
flour.
Add
all other ingredients.
Pour
into
greased bowl.
Sprinkle more cracker crumbs on top.
Dab with margarine.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until center seems done.

title: ham or corned beef oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs, milk and seasoned salt.
Tear ham or corned beef into small pieces into egg mixture.
Stir in cheese and onion.
Pour into greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish or an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Bake, uncovered, 40 to 45 minutes or until omelet is set and top is golden brown.
This is easily doubled and baked in 2 dishes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage.
Slightly beat eggs.
Add milk, salt, mustard, bread (tear into small pieces), grated Cheddar and onion. Add sausage to ingredients; mix together and pour into baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until center is firmly cooked. Stir lightly every 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not stir after removal from oven.

title: apple pudding
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart casserole.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon in bowl.
Mix well.
Add milk and butter; blend well.
Pour batter into a 2-quart casserole. Drain apples; pile in center of batter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until batter covers fruit and crust browns. Serve warm.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: carol griest's chocolate morsel strips
directions: Mix the 1 cup flour, brown sugar and butter.
Pat in bottom of greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
(It will look awful!)
Blend rest of ingredients and spread on top of baked mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes more.
(It will look great!)
Cool before cutting into squares.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: becca's enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add soup, enchilada sauce and spices and thicken with cornstarch.
Tear tortillas into 1 1/2-inch pieces. Put meat and sauce around the bottom of casserole dish.
Add layer of tortilla pieces.
Sprinkle onion, cheese and olives.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed in 3 layers.
Let cool for 5 minutes. Poke holes in cake and spoon on Cool Whip.
Dust top with cocoa or grated chocolate.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.

title: busy day beans
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add beans; stir in mustard.
Put beans in casserole in layers with sliced tomatoes, salt and sugar.
Bake 30 minutes in 400° oven.

title: congealed lime salad(weight watchers)
directions: Drain pineapple juice in a cup and add enough water to equal 1 cup.
Heat and pour over jello.
Let cool and add the rest of the ingredients.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil ingredients together (except baking powder) for 5 minutes; mix well.
Remove from heat and add baking powder; stir in quickly.
Pour over popped corn; mix well.
Put in 2 large flat pans and place in 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times.
Ad 1 package of peanuts if you like.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix and beat vigorously. In a 9 x 13 pan or 12-inch iron skillet, melt a tablespoon of Crisco or meat drippings. Pour grease into cornbread batter and mix well. Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Break up corn bread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slowly start adding chicken broth with bouillon cube dissolved in it.
Once the corn bread is moist, add onion, celery, eggs, 2 tablespoons of sage (add more, if desired) and salt and pepper to taste.
You know the corn bread is mixed just right when it is easy to fold. Too much moisture will make it soggy.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° or until top is golden brown.
Add broth every 30 minutes to keep it moist.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Cool until thickened.
Good for potato salad.
May be mixed with commercial dressing.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and take
off
of	the
bone.
Drain mixed vegetables and put in
bottom
of
oblong casserole dish.
Add chicken, onion, celery and chicken soup.
Add 1 can of chicken broth and mix together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in a bowl margarine, milk
and flour and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: lorene's chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in casserole pan.
Slice eggs on top of chicken. Pour Veg-All over this.
Mix soup and onion together and spread on top.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown beef; drain well.
Add ingredients listed, except buns, cheese and tomatoes.
Combine ingredients well.
Heat thoroughly.

title: artichoke and romaine salad
directions: Toss to combine ingredients.

title: old fashion corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients, preheat oven to 400°.
Divide cooking oil. Add part of oil to mixture; stir.
Pour into 9-inch hot skillet. Pour remaining oil over top.
Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: zucchini vegetable medley
directions: In very large skillet, melt butter.
Add green pepper, onions and celery.
Saute about 3 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, salt, sweet basil and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer about 5 minutes.
Stir in corn and tomatoes and the stewed tomatoes.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are crisp-tender.
You may serve this dish as a soup or serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Wash and drain all vegetables.
Layer them in a salad bowl in the order listed.
Spread mayonnaise on top, sealing the edges (you may use a little less than a quart).
Sprinkle cheese on top and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss right before serving
Serves 20.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add beef and brown in skillet. Drain off grease.
Pour meat mixture into a large casserole dish. Add, mixing well, the pork and beans, molasses, barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, vinegar and catsup.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: louisiana yummy
directions: Mix ingredients and spread in 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Pour all in a pan and simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken in wine sauce
directions: Roll chicken in flour mixture.
Brown in butter.
Add onion and cook until tender, but not brown.
Slice mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Add wine.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove chicken. Add half and half to skillet mixture and heat.
Pour over chicken. Serve over rice.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Mix at slow speed until moist.
Whip at high speed for at least 5 minutes.
Will keep 6 months in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: granny craver's tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugars and margarine.
Mix in eggs and flavorings.
Gradually add milk and flour to make a soft dough. Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet at 370° for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: grandma's raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins in water until plump.
Dissolve soda in 1 cup raisin water.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoons and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: valentine stained glass hearts
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat.
Stir in flour and baking powder until dough is very stiff.
Cover and chill for 3 hours or more.

title: fast fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to boil, stirring gently.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels to marshmallow mixture, stirring until melted.
Add pecans and vanilla, stirring well.
Spread evenly in 8-inch square pan. Cool and cut.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, except for cheese. Mix, then pour into buttered casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350° or until set.

title: corn chowder
directions: Put all ingredients into crock-pot, except bacon.
Heat on high for about 3 hours.
Sprinkle crumbled bacon on top of each bowl.

title: disorderly josephs(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper together.
Add 1 can soup, catsup and mustard.
Heat; serve on warm hamburger buns.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Melt margarine in a 12 x 7 1/2-inch glass baking dish.
Pour batter over melted margarine; pour peaches over batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm plain or with whipped cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pralines
directions: Use a bit pot and boil slowly to soft ball stage.
(Turns brown as it cooks.)
Be sure to stir constantly.
Take off heat and add vanilla and pecans.
Stir until candy looks creamy.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: steak diane
directions: Cook and stir onion, garlic, salt, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce in 1/4 cup butter. Stir in parsley.
Keep sauce warm.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Cook tenderloin slices over medium-high heat to medium done, about 3 or 4 minutes on each side.

title: holiday carrots
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in 3 inches water.
Drain; put in 1-quart baking dish.
Add raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally; sprinkle with almonds.

title: appetizer pizzas
directions: Combine all ingredients except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 3 pizza rounds. Spread with mixture and place on cookie sheets.
Freeze. Store in plastic bags until ready to serve. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Yields 90.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, until hot.

title: wilma's pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake in a greased and floured Bundt tube pan at 350° about 1 hour or until done.

title: white corn relish
directions: Mix Shoe Peg corn, pimentos, green pepper, onion and celery together.
Add sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and black pepper. Refrigerate.
Will keep for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: chicken bog
directions: Boil leg quarters until tender.
Take chicken off the bones. Two cups of chicken broth per cup of rice.
Salt and pepper according to taste.
Bring rice to a boil.
Cut down heat to low and cook rice 35 minutes.
Be sure to add chicken back to rice before cooking rice.

title: pizza puffs
directions: Lightly spray baking sheet with cooking spray; set aside. Separate dough into 10 pieces.
Make an indentation in the center of one piece with your thumb.
Lightly sprinkle with oregano and garlic powder.
Top with 1 cheese cube.
Pull dough over cheese and firmly pinch together so that the cheese is completely enclosed.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large pot, melt 1/4 cup butter and 2 tablespoons flour. Stir until smooth.
Add 1 cup milk and 2 cups cream (whipping). Cook until thick (about 10 minutes).
Add potatoes, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in clams and heat.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together until mixed thoroughly.
Add food coloring to make a desired color.
Keep in airtight container.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix corn flakes with 1/4 c. melted butter and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: avocado cheese dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a food processor and process until very smooth. Scrape into a pretty serving bowl and place the avocado seed in the middle. Yield: About 5 cups (plenty for a good-size party).

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart bowl and mix well.
Shape into 36 small meatballs using about 1 teaspoon for each.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Pour over vegetables and let set overnight.
Drain and serve. Save liquid to pour over leftover salad.
Keeps 3 or 4 weeks.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together butter, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and 1 cup flour; put in 8-inch square pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350 oven.

title: big boy loaf
directions: Hollow out loaf of bread.
Fill and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix crushed pretzels, melted butter or margarine and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch or 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Bake for 8 minutes; remove from oven to cool.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool in refrigerator until partially set; stir in strawberries and pecans.
While gelatin is setting, heat softened cream cheese and 1 cup sugar until smooth.
Stir in whipped topping and carefully spread over crust.
Spoon gelatin mixture over cream cheese layer. Refrigerate until firm.

title: tabitha's icing
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 minutes.
Stir in cream.
Bring to boil again. Take off heat.
Cool until lukewarm.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: frigidillies(danish meatballs)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Heat oil in pan.
Form ingredients in ball, using a medium size wet spoon.
Spoon into hot oil.
Cook slowly until brown on both sides.
Do not mash out. Great with salad.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: In measuring sugar, pack solidly in cup.
Combine sugar, butter and eggs well beaten.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt which have been mixed and sifted together, then vanilla. Roll this and shape with small cutter.
Bake at 350°.

title: miracle cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add lemon juice and cool. Cream together cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Add jello mixture and mix well.
Fold whipped Milnot into this mixture.

title: quick barbecue chicken and beans
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Place in iron skillet.
Combine Coke and ketchup and pour over chicken.
Cook on top of stove until chicken is done and Coke and ketchup becomes thick.
Remove chicken.
Add pork and beans to sauce; simmer about 15 minutes. Serve with chicken.

title: spinach cheese pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in pie crust shell (Pillsbury preformed sheets are excellent for the top; deep dish shell for bottom).
Prepare crust top with design of choice (we make leaves with trimmings), being sure to cut out a center hole and other cuts for steam release.
Baste the entire shell top with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (plus 15 minutes, depending upon oven temperature).
Rebaste after 45 minutes.
Serve cool.
Yields 12 average servings.

title: crab and pasta shells
directions: Mix ingredients together and stuff into pasta shells.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dee's fried okra
directions: Wash okra well.
Trim caps.
Slice into 1/2 inch pieces.
Soak 15 minutes in salted ice water.
Drain.
While oil is heating to 350°, roll okra in cornmeal seasoned with salt and pepper.
Dredge only a few pieces at a time, making sure to coat each piece well. Drop small batch at a time into hot oil.
Fry until okra floats on surface and is crispy golden brown.
Remove from oil with slotted spoon.
Drain on paper towels or absorbent brown paper.
To keep okra warm while frying batches, place in single layer on baking sheets lined with paper towels.
Place baking sheets in warm oven.

title: krystal's vegetable chili
directions: Melt butter; saute vegetables until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add seasonings and simmer slowly for 1/2 hour.
Add beans and salt to taste; continue to simmer for another 1/2 hour. Serve hot.
May be topped with grated cheese, if desired.
Serves 6 hearty appetites.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine first seven ingredients.
Mix well. Spread into an ungreased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Toss bread crumbs with butter;
sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour 15 minutes or until bread crumbs are golden brown and mixture is bubbly.
Sprinkle French fried onions over casserole.
Bake five minutes longer or until onions are golden.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain fat.
Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
You can prepare this salad a couple of hours ahead of time.
Add chips and dressing just before serving.

title: apple and date cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients (except dates) into a large mixing bowl.
Beat 3 to 4 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed. Stir in dates.
Drop by large teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Press a half pecan in center of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325° or 350°,
depends on oven.
Yields 6 dozen medium cookies.

title: snowy chocolate bites
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; cook over low heat until morsels and butter melt, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir until smooth.
Pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring to coat evenly.
Spread cereal mixture onto a wax paper lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; let cool one hour.
Sprinkle mixture with powdered sugar; stir to coat evenly.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening
and
sugar.
Add
eggs and beat well. Sift dry
ingredients together; add to creamed mixture, alternately with
bananas, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour
into well-greased 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Put the Doritos and salad dressing on just before you serve the salad.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles until completely done. Drain; combine noodles, tuna, mayonnaise, vegetables and salt. Blend soup and milk by heating. Add cheese and heat until cheese melts. Add noodle mixture. Turn into a large baking dish. Bake at 300° about 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: snow cream
directions: Okay, you
find clean, white snow.
You scoop it into a big pan.
Pour
in
a little milk, enough to pack the snow but not enough to
melt the snow.
Add some vanilla.
You know how you like it!
Throw
in
an
egg or two.
How big is your pot? You may need three.
Stir it all up.
Call the kids and enjoy.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all together well and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: onion soup
directions: Slice onions very thin.
Saute in butter until light brown. Heat stock (if using bouillon, add an equal amount of water).
Add to onions and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add salt.
Place toast slice in individual serving dishes.
Add soup and sprinkle with the grated Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving liquid; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in reserved fruit liquid and chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in next 3 ingredients. Pour into a lightly oiled 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Yields 8 servings.

title: alabama salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Set in refrigerator until set.

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix sugar, whole eggs and oil well. Sift dry ingredients into egg mixture. Add nuts and carrots. Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until done. Makes 3 loaves.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In mixer beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in oil and vanilla.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Skin chicken and cut up.
Let Broccoli unthaw and cut up.
Mix chicken and broccoli together.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: pretzel gelatin salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to directions on box. Refrigerate until it is set enough to add fruit and marshmallows without them sinking to bottom of pan. While Jell-O is setting, prepare rest of mixture. Cream sugar and margarine. Mix with pretzels. Pat lightly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Cream package of cream cheese with scant cup of granulated sugar. Fold in small carton of confectioners sugar. Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled crust. If Jell-O is set enough by now to add fruit and marshmallows, do so and spread all the mixture over the top of cheese mixture. Refrigerate overnight or until firm.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Slice strawberries.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and let stand 1 hour.
Heat oven to 450°.
Grease layer pans and flour.
Mix flour and 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like meal.
Stir in milk and blend well.
Pour into pans and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Split layers while warm.
Spread with strawberries and stack layers.
Top with berries and whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: luree's ham spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed in boiling water.
Meanwhile, saute in margarine the ham, chives and mushrooms, stirring often.
Drain cooked spaghetti and add ham, chives, mushrooms, whipping cream and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Cook on low heat for 10 more minutes and serve with salad.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fiesta dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Combine with sausage.
Drain tomatoes and break up.
Mix with cheese and sausage.

title: french pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cook over medium heat.
Flip when top starts bubbling.

title: no-peek chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot. Stir well. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours or until chicken is done. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit well in collander.
Mix all ingredients and chill for 12 hours in refrigerator.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes and soups.
Mix well.
Layer chicken and tortillas in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add soup mixture, then onion and cheese. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut tops from 4 large green peppers and remove seeds.
Place peppers in a large pan of boiling, salted water and boil, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes, turning once (just until cooked, but not too soft to handle for filling).
Combine ham and rice and fill pepper shells.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve plain or topped with white sauce.

title: crouton chicken
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Pour mushroom soup over chicken.
Sprinkle on Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
The last 15 minutes sprinkle on croutons.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and margarine (soften margarine in microwave).
Press in greased 11 x 14-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese yummies(student favorite)
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread flat one can of crescent rolls. Mix cheese, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Spread mixture on bottom crust.
Spread the second can of crescent rolls on top of cheese mixture.
Brush egg white on top and sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Combine buttermilk and soda in a 5-quart saucepan, stirring until soda is dissolved; add sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt. Bring mixture to a boil; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and pecans to candy; beat until mixture begins to thicken and loses its gloss.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a lightly buttered baking sheet or waxed paper; let stand until firm.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
About 18 pralines.

title: easy crab soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with biscuits, bread or crackers.
This is easy and very good.

title: mediterranean couscous salad
directions: Bring stock to boil in small saucepan.
Mix couscous.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff couscous with fork.
Turn into medium bowl.
Cool to room temperature.

title: helen's ginger creams
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and mix well.
Add molasses and water to which baking soda has been added.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture; mix well.
Pour batter into two large cookie sheets. Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Frost with a powdered sugar icing while warm.
Cut into desired sizes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Add whole milk if necessary to fill freezer 3/4 full.
Add all ingredients and freeze according to directions on ice cream maker. Makes 6 quarts.

title: easy coleslaw
directions: Chop cabbage up in food processor, very finely.
Sprinkle sugar and salt over cabbage.
Leave for 1 minute.

title: lo-cal cucumbers
directions: Chill thinly sliced cucumbers.
Toss lightly with remaining ingredients.
Quickens appetite.
No calories to count.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Bring tomatoes to boil, add Jell-O and stir until dissolved. Add cold water and a dash of Tabasco.
Congeal in refrigerator.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and sugar. Add pineapple chunks and fruit cocktail; add marshmallows and pecans. Mix well with Cool Whip. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower, bacon, onion, tomatoes and eggs.
Set aside.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put 1/2 cookie crumbs into 9 x 13-inch pan and press.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar, then add Cool Whip.
Blend well and set aside.
Mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Combine with cream cheese mixture and mix well.
Pour mixture over crumbs and top with remaining crumbs.
Chill in freezer.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Salt
and
pepper
inside dressed poultry, then boil in enough water
to
cover
and cook until tender.
Take chicken from broth here
and
let
cool and remove bones and then put meat back into
broth.
Be
sure
to
have at least 3 cups of water remaining
after poultry has cooked.
If less than this remains, add enough hot water to make up the difference.
Add 1/4 cup butter.

title: quick cake
directions: Pour over top of batter a mixture of brown sugar, white sugar and salt; over all pour boiling water.
If chocolate sauce is desired, add 1 tablespoon cocoa to sugar topping.
Bake at 350°.

title: cabbage stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry cabbage, carrots and onion in margarine until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients; stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Serve over chow mein noodles or rice, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: donuts
directions: Mix water, potatoes, yeast, sugar and salt; let set for 20 minutes.
Add egg, oil and flour, mixing well.
Let rise until double.
Work again; roll out and cut.
Let rise until double again.
Cook in hot oil.

title: poncho punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.
A very pretty, delicious and refreshing punch.

title: raspberry squares or strawberry
directions: Line a pan (8 x 8-inch) with pie pastry.
Spread with raspberry or strawberry jam.
Mix the ingredients and spread over all.
Bake at 375° until brown, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In skillet, melt butter.
Add onion, bell pepper and carrots.
Stir and cook for 5 minutes.
Mix in ketchup, pineapple juice, vinegar, sugar, soy sauce, garlic powder, salt, pepper and ginger.
Stir constantly until mixture boils.
Add pineapple chunks.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sweet and sour sauce over chicken.
