Bake covered for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice into bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover lightly.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: our favorite baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole or bean pot.
(The bacon can be partially fried if you prefer.)
Bake at 350°. Cover for first 30 minutes of baking time and uncover for last 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin swirl
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Line top and sides with wax paper.
Grease wax paper.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan and spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes.
Invert onto towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Peel off waxed paper.
Roll up cake in towel together from short side.
Place seam side down on wire rack. Cool completely.
Unroll.
Spread with filling.
Reroll and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, eggs and soda/buttermilk.
Add flour and spices.
Mix, saving 1/4 cup flour to mix with fruit and nuts. Add fruit, nuts and cooking sherry to flour mixture.
With a teaspoon, drop on a cookie sheet in small balls.
Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
You don't have to bake all at one time.

title: lemon - pineapple pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together undrained pineapple and dry lemon pudding mix.
In another bowl, prepare Dream Whip according to package instructions.
Gently fold Dream Whip into pineapple - pudding mixture.
Turn into graham cracker crust.
Chill several hours.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Combine sugar, flour and nuts.
Pour melted butter until blended.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 11 1/2 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.
Cool and cut.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: chicken elizabeth
directions: In electric blender, combine all ingredients and blend until creamy with semi-cooled pan juice.
Drizzle over chicken, cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Heat pineapple and sugar until sugar is dissolved and add to jello.
Refrigerate to chill until syrupy.
Then add cottage cheese, Cool Whip and pecans pieces; refrigerate until firm.
This is a double batch.

title: microwave peanut butter brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, peanuts, and salt in a deep 3-quart casserole; mix well.
Microwave at HIGH for 8 1/2 minutes or until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla, mixing well.
Microwave for 1 minute or until mixture reaches hard crack stage (300 degrees). Stir in soda; pour onto a buttered cookie sheet, spreading thinly. Let cool.
Break into pieces.
Yield:
about 1 pound.

title: choco banana bars
directions: Melt chocolate; cool.
Combine margarine, sugar, bananas, egg, milk, bran and nuts and beat until smooth.
Add dry ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
May frost with creamy chocolate icing.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.

title: country style steak
directions: Pound flour, which has been seasoned with salt and pepper, into cube or round steak.
Brown on both sides in small amount of oil.
To make gravy, add water to meat and allow to simmer until meat is done.
Thicken water gravy with milk and flour paste.

title: white house cowboy cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a bowl. In another large bowl, beat butter until smooth and creamy. Gradually beat in sugars and combine well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each. Beat in vanilla. Stir in flour mixture until just combined. Add chocolate chips, oats, coconut and pecans. For each cookie, drop 1/4 cup of dough onto ungreased baking sheets, spacing 3-inches apart. Bake 15 to 20 minutes, rotating sheet halfway through. Remove cookies to rack to cool.

title: surprise cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together.
In another bowl, combine ingredients and stir with a fork until blended.
Line muffin tins with foil papers.
Put 1 tablespoon of batter in each foil cup.
Place 1/2 of fun sized Snickers (or your favorite) and cover with 1 additional tablespoon of batter.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potatoes parmesan(great for leftover spuds)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Coat baking pan with Pam.
Using 2 spoons, drop on pan. Sprinkle on 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: bean and cheese chili
directions: Heat oil in a 2 to 3-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add onions and green pepper and, stirring often, cook 5 to 6 minutes until onions are clear.
Stir in tomatoes, cumin, oregano, garlic, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium low and simmer uncovered about 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir in beans; simmer 15 minutes longer until beans are hot and chili has thickened slightly.
Stir in black pepper.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with cheese and cilantro.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix slowly with rotary beater until just blended.
Pour into crust and chill.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs. Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, margarine and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then egg and vanilla.
Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Glaze or garnish as desired.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: chocolate caramel squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Measure 2 tablespoons chocolate flavor syrup; reserve.
Mix brownie mix, remaining syrup, water and egg with spoon just until mix is moistened.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 27 to 30 minutes (do not overbake).

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, shortening, mashed bananas and flour. Mix well, then add nuts.
Set oven at 350° and bake for 60 to 70 minutes in loaf pan (greased and floured).

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream
butter;
add cheese, then salt, pepper and flour. Roll into
tiny
balls.
Press half pecan on each ball to flatten. Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven. Makes 40 to 45 cookies; 50 calories for 4 cookies.

title: apple salad dressing
directions: Mix egg, sugar and flour.
Add 1 cup of boiling water.
Cook until it thickens.
Add lemon juice.
Pour over chopped apples and pecans.
The salad dressing will keep for about two weeks in the refrigerator.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, nuts and bananas. Add sifted flour and soda.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked reuben chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place sauerkraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese. Pour dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours or until fork can be inserted easily. Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Separate roll dough into 4 rectangles.
Seal seams well. Place 1/2 apple in center and seal dough completely.
Place in lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Pour orange juice into dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Serve hot with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix jelly and chili sauce together. Set aside. Soak bread in milk. Mix ground beef, salt, pepper, garlic salt and bread together.
Shape in small balls and place in mixture of jelly and chili sauce.
Bake in 375 degree oven for 1 hour.

title: mama's jello salad
directions: Mix together jellos and boiling water until dissolved. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and chill until set.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together with mixer:
shortening, sugar, vanilla and almond.
Add 1 egg and milk.
Mix in flour with hands.
Divide in half.
Let stay in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Spray Pam in pan.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: double crusted lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Place top crust and flute the edges.
Cut vent hole in top crust. Brush top crust with egg and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 minutes.

title: basic cheese sauce
directions: Combine and chill.
One tablespoon contains 10 calories.
Use as a dip for crackers or vegetables.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
These can be frozen unbaked.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O by directions on box.
Crush cranberry sauce with fork and add Jell-O.
Add other ingredients and let congeal.

title: italian dream cake
directions: Cream butter and margarine.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift together the flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and pecans. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with your favorite filling or frosting.

title: simple chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add seasoning, beans, tomatoes. Bring to a boil and then simmer for about 20 minutes.
You can top with chopped onions and grated cheese.

title: buckeyes
directions: Thoroughly blend powdered sugar, Jif, butter, vanilla and salt.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Place chocolate pieces and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Heat over boiling water until chocolate and paraffin are melted.
Insert toothpick into candy ball; dip 1/2 of the ball into melted chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper until set.
Smooth over toothpick holes.

title: all-natural beef jerky
directions: Trim off all fat from one round steak.
Cut meat into thin strips and place in oblong pan.
Combine the next 7 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Cool, pour liquid over meat through strainer.
Let sit in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Remove marinated pieces and lay across a broiling pan.
Put strips into cold oven and set the temperature at 125°.
Dry meat in oven 10 to 12 hours.
Store in a covered container.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim off fat.
Semi-freeze meat and slice with grain, approximately 2 inches long and 1/2 inch thick.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except last 2.
Grease 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Pour in mixture; spread evenly.
Mix together 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle over mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions, omitting water.
Press into pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until golden.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar in bowl; mix with mixer until well blended.
Spread over warm crust.
Cut up fruit; arrange decoratively on crust. Pour on glaze.

title: energy bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large frying pan, combine cereal, oats and sesame seed.
Toast over medium heat for a few minutes until crisp, stirring constantly.

title: tenderloin au sherry
directions: Salt and pepper tenderloin and brown in hot fat in skillet. After it is good and brown on all sides, add 1/2-inch of water in your skillet.
Place lid on and turn fire down low.
Cook for about 1 hour, adding water if necessary.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar and nuts. Sprinkle over top of batter. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes. Remove from oven and spread with topping.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water until syrupy.
Fold in fruits and juices.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Fold in topping, making a marbled effect.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Divide apple slices between 2 custard cups. Sprinkle water over apple slices.
Mix flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon with a fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake, uncovered, until topping is lightly golden brown and apples are tender, approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese and soup.
Pour into a large casserole.
On top of mixture spread soup and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: baked lasagna casserole
directions: In a large heavy pan, brown ground beef in oil with onion, garlic and parsley. Add tomato paste, 2 cups water, salt and pepper and simmer for 1 hour.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: Combine butter and Crisco; cream well.
Add sugar, cream well. Beat eggs separately then add to butter mixture.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use tube pan.

title: spanish sauce
directions: Fry the onion in the oil over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add the spices; simmer for 3 minutes.
Add green chiles, stewed tomatoes and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Thicken the sauce with the flour, then simmer for 20 more minutes.

title: rolled cutout cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Beat in egg, cream and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt until well mixed. If desired, chill dough for about an hour.

Preheat oven to 400°. Roll out dough, 1/3 at a time, onto floured surface to 1/8 inch thick. Cut into shapes. Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheets. If desired, sprinkle with sugar. Bake 5 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sand
directions: Make pudding according to package.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Mix in vanilla wafers.
Save some to sprinkle on top.
Chill.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Place spaghetti sauce in saucepan on low to thoroughly heat. Boil shells according to package directions; use 1 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon oil in water. Mix all remaining ingredients together until you have a consistent concoction. Once shells soften, drain and run cold water over them; allow to drain again. Stuff cheese mixture into shell until bursting. Place shells in rows in 2 Pyrex 9 x 13-inch pans. Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until tops of shells turn light brown. Ladle sauce over shells per individual taste.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in saucepan over low to medium heat. Add sugar, nuts and cocoa. Stir well and knead. Pat out onto greased (with margarine) platter. Let set until firm. Cut into small squares. Makes approximately 5 1/2 pounds.

title: puffy french toast
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend milk and egg.
Add to flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Dip bread slices into batter, turning to coat sides evenly.
Fry in preheated 375° deep fat until golden brown, about 2 minutes on both sides.
Drain and serve hot.

title: pecan watercress salad with pears and bleu cheese(source:  santa fe recipe)
directions: Arrange the watercress in a circle in the center of a large plate.
Fan out the julienned pears around the edges.
Sprinkle the salad with the Bleu cheese and pecans.
In a small bowl, place the vinegar, olive oil, white pepper, sugar and salt.
Whisk everything together until the dressing is well blended.
Dribble the dressing over the salad.
Serves 4.
Easy to make; very tasty!

title: old fashioned soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift together twice the flour, baking soda, spices and salt. Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg, sour cream and molasses.
Stir in flour mixture and mix until blended.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Pat or roll to a sheet about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with a cookie cutter.
Bake on an ungreased sheet at 350° to 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: shrimp mold or spread
directions: Heat soup, cream cheese and small can shrimp (drained).
Add gelatin (dissolved in 3 tablespoons water), celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Mix by hand slowly.
Needs 8 hours to set in mold.

title: baked scallops with orange sections
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put sea scallops in a 9-inch baking dish and drizzle with olive oil.
Cut orange sections from the white membrane over the baking dish so the juice is saved.
Arrange orange sections among scallops and bake for 8 minutes.
Add bay scallops and sprinkle with dill.
Broil for 4 minutes.

title: pizza cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-inch pizza pan.
Combine butter, brown sugar, vanilla, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread evenly in pan, leaving a 1 to 2-inch border.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: cheddarburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into a loaf (8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inches) in shallow baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ricotta lasagna swirls
directions: Steam spinach until limp and chop.
Mix spinach with cheeses, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Coat each noodle with 2 to 3 tablespoons of the mixture along its entire length.
Roll the noodle up; turn on end so you can see the spiral and place in a shallow baking pan.
Pour homemade or canned spaghetti sauce over the rolled up noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put garlic, hot pepper pod and dill in jars.
Then fill quart jars with cucumbers.
Mix vinegar, salt and water.
Then pour brine to 1 inch of top.
Seal jars completely.
Bake in a 350° oven until the pickles turn a pale green.

title: pastry for 2-crust pie
directions: Sift flour and salt together into bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until particles are the size of peas.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Mix lightly with a fork.
Gather dough together with fingers and form into a ball.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
After draining, mix with some of the Salad Supreme.
Add onions and salad dressing, then tomatoes and cucumbers.
Mix well; chill.
Mix well before serving.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in ungreased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: beef, corn and tomatoes
directions: Brown beef in oil.
Stir to break up meat into bite size pieces.
Add onion and green pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.
Cook 2 cups of Minute rice per directions.
Serve beef mixture over rice.
Quick, easy, delicious. Store leftover in refrigerator.
Reheat 3 to 4 minutes in microwave covered with wax paper or Saran Wrap.
If preferred, serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Work slices cucumbers; onions and salt together in a large bowl with your hands until mixed well. Cover and refrigerate for 2-3 hours. Drain off juice. Add Miracle Whip, vinegar and sugar (small amount...1 packet of Equal works well) and stir until creamy. Sprinkle top with pepper, parsley or paprika, as you wish. Cover and refrigerate. Keeps well and can be made a day ahead. Tastes better the longer it sits.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix meats, dry bread crumbs, carrot, onion and eggs.
Add milk, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly.
Place on a double thick square of greased aluminum foil.
Shape into a 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Saute mushrooms and 1 tablespoon onion in butter over medium heat.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Spread stuffing over meat.
Roll up, starting at long edge.
Press overlapping edge into roll to seal. Bring foil edges together in a tight double fold on top.
Fold ends up using tight double folds.
Place wrapped meat loaf on rack in shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Open foil and continue baking 15 minutes or until loaf browns.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Stir together the preserves, honey, onion soup mix and French dressing.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can use orange marmalade, peach or pineapple preserves.
This can be used over pork, too.

title: veal piccata
directions: Cut veal into large pieces.
Dip into lightly salted flour to coat.
Saute veal in butter until browned.
(I do it in 2 batches and only use butter as needed.)
Remove veal from pan.
Add chicken broth and scrape essence.
Add wine to taste.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder.
Return veal to pan and simmer 1/2 hour until tender.
Put veal servings on plates.
Add lemon juice to essence to taste.
Pour essence over individual servings and sprinkle lightly with fresh pepper.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Melt butter in shallow pan.
Break up vermicelli into pieces and fry in butter until slightly brown, stirring constantly.
Wash and drain rice well, then add to vermicelli and saute together for a few minutes (keep stirring), then add boiling broth and salt; cover and cook on low fire for 20 minutes.
When water is all absorbed and rice is soft, take off fire.
Let rest for 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Stir once more with fork.
(Serves 4.)

title: super easy casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Boil potatoes and onion until done.
Stir beef with potatoes and onion with cream of mushroom soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: capri sun freeze
directions: Place juice pack in the freezer. Cut the top off when frozen. Push out as popsicle. (Great when sick.)

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini, onion and bell pepper in 1/2 to 1 stick of margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry walnut bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients; stir in orange juice, orange peel and melted margarine.
Toss together egg, blueberries, walnuts and 1/4 cup flour; stir into batter.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: quick potatoes divine
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix all ingredients with potatoes.
Pour in a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Save enough cheese for the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large bowl, combine eggs, milk, mustard and salt. Distribute half of bread evenly in a buttered 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish. Sprinkle half pepper, half cheese, half sausage and half of each optional ingredient. Repeat layering, using remaining bread, pepper, cheese, sausage and optional ingredients. Pour egg mixture over casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 55 to 60 minutes until eggs are set. Makes 6 servings.

title: brown bag biscuits
directions: Combine spices and sugar in paper bag. Separate
the refrigerator biscuits and cut into quarters.
Put quarters into oleo. Drop into spice bag and shake.
Put into an 8-inch round greased baking dish in one layer. Put remaining spices and melted oleo over top.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown. Serve warm. Makes 40 bite size biscuits.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cut potatoes into wedges.
Toss potatoes and all other ingredients together until well coated.
Place into roasting pan and bake at 450° for 1 hour 10 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cracker scallops
directions: Dry scallops in paper towels.
Season with pepper.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until very hot.
Add scallops, then garlic to skillet.
Immediately add tomatoes and toss.
Add crackers, lemon juice, 2 tablespoons of parsley and butter.
Cook and stir until scallops are cooked through and crackers are browned.
Garnish with remaining parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut blossoms(cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed except for candy kisses.
Shape dough into small balls, roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 11 to 12 minutes at 375 degrees.
When removed from oven, immediately top with a candy kiss.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: rebecca's zoo food
directions: In a medium bowl, mix crackers, peanuts, candy and dates. Store in an airtight container or in a reclosable plastic bag. Makes about 3 3/4 cups.

title: tennessee pride chili
directions: Saute sausage, ground beef, onion, green pepper and garlic in large heavy saucepan until browned, stirring to crumble sausage. Drain off excess grease.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Break tomatoes with back of wooden spoon.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Additional water may be added, if needed.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Pour into shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 425°.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake another 30 or more minutes.

title: rice cereal sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in shortening until it resembles coarse meal. Add vinegar and 1/2 cup milk all at once, stirring only to combine. Turn out on slightly floured board.
Knead gently 5 or 6 times.
Divide dough into 16 equal parts. Roll each on board with palm of hand to 6-inch cylinder.
Brush with remaining milk. Combine cereal, salt and caraway or poppy seed.
Roll each in cereal.
Place on sheet and bake 15 minutes.

title: raspberry surprise
directions: Whip up the cream until stiff.
Fold into it the heaped spoonfuls of powdered sugar.
Gently fold in the raspberries and about half a bag of marshmallows (use your own judgment with regards to the raspberries and marshmallows).
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve chilled in Sunday dishes.
Very good after a hot, spicy meal.
Serves 6 to 8 or more!

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring to a boil, then cook the sugar, milk, butter and cocoa 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat all together.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, water and salt in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook until mixture forms a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream.
Stir until slightly thick.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Fold until stiff.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper greased with butter or margarine.

title: mexican flour shells
directions: Cream everything together.
Spread over flour tortillas.
Roll up and slice in 2 to 3-inch pieces.
Serve with salsa.

title: rosemary lamb shanks
directions: Put shanks in casserole large enough to be in single layer. Add garlic, rosemary, wine, salt and pepper.
Cover casserole with foil and a lid.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove shanks to warm plates.
Cook down liquid until thickened slightly.
Pour over meat and serve.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Put water, brown sugar, raisins, shortening, salt and spices in a saucepan.
Mix.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Cool. Sift together flour, soda and baking powder.
Stir into cooled mixture, mixing well.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Frost, if desired, or serve plain.

title: fig preserves
directions: Cook figs in small amount of water and mash.
Add sugar and bring to a boil.
Then add jello.
Boil 3 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: meatball yummies
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg and 2 tablespoons Prime Choice steak sauce.
Mix and shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in oil; drain fat.
Combine 1/3 cup Prime Choice steak sauce, brown sugar and butter with meatballs in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes or until done.
Excellent hors d'oeuvres served with toothpicks.

title: stripped delight
directions: Combine crumbs with sugar and melted butter.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 5 minutes and bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Cool.
Beat cream cheese with sugar and 2 tablespoons milk until smooth.
Fold in half of the Cool Whip.
Spread over crust. Prepare pudding, using 3 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over cream cheese. Chill several hours or overnight.
Spread remaining Cool Whip. Makes 12 servings.

title: husband's delight(hamburger-cheese bake)
directions: Combine beef, garlic, salt, pepper, sugar and tomato sauce in skillet.
Bring to boil; simmer 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and onions.

title: quick strawberry "short" cake
directions: Wash, stem and partially crush berries; add sugar.
Break crackers into 4 pieces.
Add to berries as you would a baked pie crust.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/4 can of noodles.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with the rest of the noodles and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add egg and beat well.
Add flour mixed with soda, salt and spices alternately with buttermilk.
Add nuts, raisins, dates and prunes.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package, using 3 cups milk.
Fold in whipping cream.
Reserve 6 wafers and 1 banana.
Slice remaining bananas.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in 2-quart glass bowl. Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave 8 minutes on Cookmatic level 8 or until thickened, stirring twice with wire whisk.
(I stir after 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.)
Stir a little of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Blend warm yolks into hot mixture.
Microwave 2 minutes longer on "8" or until custard coats a metal spoon, stirring once. Stir in butter and vanilla.
Top with meringue or whipped topping.

title: shrimp pie
directions: Open crescent rolls; set aside one roll.
Make a pie shell in a deep dish pie pan with the remaining rolls.
Mix shrimp and cheese; place into pie.
Use remaining roll to make strips for the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together.
It will be real stiff.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry-vanilla pudding
directions: Place angel food cake on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In mixer on low speed, add pudding, milk and ice cream. Blend until well mixed.
Spread pudding mixture over angel food cake and chill until set, about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion together, then add rice.
Add to broccoli mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Put almonds on top, mix together everything and bake at 350° for 30 minutes with cheese on top.

title: baked fruit medley
directions: Layer fruit and nuts in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar and flour well and sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: Combine ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat until desired thickness is reached.
Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Let cool.
Pour into sterilized jars and refrigerate. Good on homemade hot biscuits.

title: simple chicken casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole, heat milk and cheese until milk is hot. Add remaining ingredients.
Top with saltine cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes, covered.
Uncover for 10 minutes.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Stew the first five ingredients with water until chicken can easily be removed from the bone.
Reserve 2 cups liquid until later.
Remove all bones and skin.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and arrange on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange drained mushrooms on top of chicken.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a bowl, mix cake mix according to directions on package. Set aside.

title: cornflour cookies (1)
directions: Roll on floured surface.

title: oven roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add in all other ingredients.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender with salt.
Layer cabbage, soup and end with cheese on top.
Top with saltines and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: "24 hour slaw"
directions: Put vinegar, sugar, salt and oil in saucepan.
Bring to boil, pour over chopped cabbage and onion mix.
Let cool.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours or longer.
Eat and enjoy!

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook frozen vegetables in 1 cup of water, covered, for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare pans.
In a large bowl, combine shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, baking powder and spices.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake about 70 minutes or until done.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onion until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper to form smooth paste.
Gradually add milk.
Beat, stirring until thickened.
Add chicken and pour sauce over broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crushed potato chips. Place in baking dish.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbles and chips are brown.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; add peanut butter, blending with fork.
Stir in milk and egg.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Makes 1 (9 x 5-inch) loaf.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook on low, medium heat, stirring continuously, until thick. Serve over ice cream.

title: frankly fancy
directions: Mix together flour, butter and nuts.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: coconut-macadamia nut cakes
directions: Blend together butter, sugars and eggs.
Mix in flour, soda, salt (if used), vanilla and water. Stir in coconut and nuts. Drop by teaspoons onto baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil until the beans are thick.
Mash beans.
Pour into a dish that the beans will be in a thin layer.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: cowboy baked beans
directions: Chop onions and green pepper and saute in butter until limp. Set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onions and pepper mixture and allow to simmer on low for 10 minutes until dry. Drain, if necessary.

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; beat on low speed of mixer until well blended.
Cover; refrigerate dough 1 to 2 hours.
Remove wrappers from Kisses.
Heat oven to 375°.
Using 1 tablespoon of dough for each cookie, shape dough around each Kiss; roll to make ball. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until cookies are set, but not brown. Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole pan with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
A box of frozen corn may be used.
Cook it about 2 minutes before mixing.

title: applesauce bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine bread and milk in a bowl.
Mix until bread is thoroughly soaked.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: baked beans-hamburger casserole
directions: Saute bacon and onions together.
Brown ground beef with them. Add remainder of ingredients and mix together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sausage and rice bake
directions: Cook sausage until brown and crumbly, drain and set aside. Combine rice and 1-1/2 cups of cheese. Spread rice mixture in greased 12 x 8 x 2 baking dish, sprinkle with sausage. Combine soup and milk, pour over sausage, sprinkle with crumbled bacon and the remaining cheese and cover with bread crumbs (as desired). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can also be frozen for later date.

title: mobile red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans.
Combine all ingredients in large pot with plenty of water.
Cook until beans are tender (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Serve on rice.

title: swiss steak
directions: Flour steak and brown in fat.
Mix other ingredients and cook in pressure cooker about 45 minutes or in a conventional cooker, about 2 hours.

title: quicky cherry cobbler
directions: Pour cherries into a bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and let stand. Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour this batter over the butter in casserole. Add cherries.
Do not mix or stir.
The batter will rise to the top during baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sausage tortellini soup
directions: Cook Italian sausage. Add onion and garlic and saut. In a large saucepan, add beef broth, water, wine, tomatoes, tomato sauce, green pepper and spices. When ready, add sausage mixture. Add carrots and zucchini 20 to 30 minutes prior to serving. Before serving, bring to a boil and add tortellini. Let boil for 8 to 10 minutes, then serve.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill about 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar, crisscross.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Cool completely.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken fried rice
directions: Cut pepper and onion before cooking.
Can use ham, pork or beef, even lobster and shrimp combined together if you like.
Cook 1 cup steam rice.
Heat the frypan.
Pour a little oil on it.
Put rice and chicken, pepper and onion in the frypan and stir it.
Add sugar, salt and soy sauce.
Stir until it is done.
Makes 1 to 2 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Add squash, onions and salt; cover with ice.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Combine the sugar, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric; boil together.
Drain squash and onions; dip in cold water to remove some of the salt, then add to boiling vinegar. Boil for 2 to 3 minutes, put into jars and seal.

title: pork cutlets viennese style
directions: Pound pork cutlets until very thin.
Season lightly with salt and pepper.
Dip in beaten egg and then in bread crumbs.
Heat skillet with equal amounts butter and oil until hot.
Quickly fry the cutlets on both sides until evenly brown.
Serve with a garnish of lemon wedges, German potato salad and a tossed green salad.

title: pecan logs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy. Beat in flour and salt. Add vanilla. Fold in pecans. Shape into logs. Lay on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes until slightly golden. Remove from cookie sheet and roll at once in confectioners sugar. Cool and roll in confectioners sugar again. Makes approximately 42 logs.

title: cabbage and beef soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown beef. Add all remaining ingredients except parsley. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Garnish with parsley. Yields 3 quarts. Soup can be frozen.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit very well.
Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
A good and easy make ahead recipe.
Stores well and is always ready to serve.

title: cranberry glazed ham
directions: Arrange orange slices and whole cloves on ham.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes per pound.
During the last 40 minutes, brush with a mixture of remaining ingredients.

title: never fail popcorn balls
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows together.
Pour over popcorn. Shape into balls.
Serve.
Yields 24 balls.

title: lemon-nut vegetable mold
directions: Put gelatin in medium bowl.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cold water, wine vinegar, lemon juice, salt and onion salt.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Fold in nuts, celery, cucumber, radishes and peas.
Turn into 1-quart mold.
Chill 2 hours or until firm. Turn out on lettuce-lined plate or platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot dogs in cornmeal batter
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, dry mustard, baking powder, salt, oil, milk and egg.
This will make one cup of batter.
Dry frankfurters on paper towel and insert wooden skewer in end of frankfurter.
Dip in batter, coating completely.
Pour batter into tall glass for easy coating.
Fry in deep hot fat at 375° until golden brown, about 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: yummies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add the egg, vanilla, flour, soda and salt. Roll into 1-inch balls (leave as a ball) and put into greased small muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: one casserole meal
directions: Brown hamburger, meat and onion.
Layer meat in greased 2-quart casserole.
Layer alternately with potatoes and peas.
Top with tomato soup.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° to 350° until golden brown.
Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: cheesecake strawberry sauce
directions: Process strawberries in food processor or blender until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and Equal, refrigerate until serving time.
Makes about 2 cups.
